{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778722960530,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\ntitle: Gate ALU multiplications by opcode to reduce combinational area\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The ALU unconditionally computes three 32x32 signed/unsigned products on every\ncycle regardless of the actual instruction. On FPGA this inflates the combinational\nfootprint (~3000+ LUTs for multiplier trees), increases routing congestion, and\ndegrades timing closure. CoreMark frequently exercises the ALU for address arithmetic\nand logic operations, but M-extension multiplies are relatively rare. Reducing the\nalways-active multiplier logic should improve median Fmax by easing place-and-route.\nhypothesis: |\n  Restructure `alu.sv` so that `mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, and `mul_su` are assigned only\nwhen the current `op` is a multiply instruction. Move the multiplication expressions\ninside the main `case (op)` arm (or guard them with an outer `if`) so the synthesis\ntool sees they are dead for non-M instructions. This explicitly prunes unused\nmultiplier instantiation without changing the pipeline latency or functional results.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: Guard the three 32x32 multiplier computations with the ALU opcode so they are only evaluated for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU instructions.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778722960515,"end":1778722960529}},"id":"prt_e2426548d001ak79ksxTpRoxNL","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","messageID":"msg_e24246c8d002xfiJX1g3RYO728"}}
