{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778722965328,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","part":{"id":"prt_e2426874d001McZwPK1BxmXyh6","messageID":"msg_e2426795d002DcoJ9BChqdKjSz","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","snapshot":"0b3f25d1794abfb66724329a0ee3825d0cb93907","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778722970242,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","part":{"id":"prt_e24268c3b001KGp30sjy2T3W6j","messageID":"msg_e2426795d002DcoJ9BChqdKjSz","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c68ffe0NE0VSmrtvPYD0","type":"text","text":"I've written the hypothesis file to:\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** `micro_opt`\n- **Idea:** Gate the three 32×32 multiplier computations in `rtl/alu.sv` so they are only evaluated when the ALU opcode is actually a multiply instruction (`MUL*` ops). Currently `mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, and `mul_su` are computed unconditionally on every cycle, inflating combinational area and FPGA routing congestion.\n- **Expected impact:** ~4% fitness improvement (medium confidence), primarily through better Fmax from reduced LUT count and improved place-and-route.","time":{"start":1778722966587,"end":1778722970239}}}
