{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778725083491,"sessionID":"ses_1dbbd8624ffegC9E6f6kSZD0gl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\ntitle: MEM-to-EX load bypass to eliminate load-use stalls\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\n  because it can only forward loaded data from MEM/WB, not from the MEM stage\n  itself.  CoreMark pointer-chasing and array-index patterns frequently emit a\n  LOAD followed immediately by a dependent ALU or STORE.  Eliminating the\n  load-use bubble improves IPC with no extra pipeline stages or tables.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a combinational bypass from mem_stage's load_data output back to the\n  EX-stage operand muxes.  Extend the forwarding_unit so that when EX/MEM\n  contains a LOAD whose rd matches an EX-stage rs, it selects the new bypass\n  path (encoding 2'b11).  Remove the load_use_hazard stall from hazard_unit;\n  the bypass makes it unnecessary.  All other stalls (imem/dmem backpressure,\n  redirect flush) remain unchanged.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 7\n  confidence: high\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >-\n      Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id.\n      The MEM→EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: >-\n      Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and\n      ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the\n      MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to\n      select fwd_mem_load when the forwarding select is 2'b11.\n  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n    description: >-\n      Expose the combinational load_data signal as a new output port\n      load_data_fwd [31:0] so core.sv can route it back to ex_stage.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >-\n      Wire mem_stage.load_data_fwd to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load.  Connect\n      ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.  Update the\n      hazard_unit instantiation to reflect removed load-use stall logic.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778725083472,"end":1778725083490}},"id":"prt_e2446a7d10018xVz5cyg26xvXs","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd8624ffegC9E6f6kSZD0gl","messageID":"msg_e24427a18001ymQMeUha6yxctA"}}
