{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778726978781,"sessionID":"ses_1db9e25c4ffeWL056lNnlwtuko","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\ntitle: Eliminate false load-use stalls via opcode-aware hazard detection\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\n  (instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\n  regardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\n  For I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\n  field is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\n  ADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\n  spurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\n  so false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\n  Eliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add opcode decoding to hazard_unit so load-use detection only fires when\n  the instruction in ID actually reads rs1/rs2 as registers. R-type, I-type\n  (OP-IMM/LOAD/JALR), S-type, and B-type use rs1; R-type, S-type, and B-type\n  use rs2. U-type and J-type use neither. This removes false stalls without\n  altering pipeline structure or lengthening critical paths.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: Add opcode input and uses_rs1/uses_rs2 qualification to the load_use_hazard check.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: Wire if_id_w.instr[6:0] to the hazard_unit's new opcode input.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778726978770,"end":1778726978780}},"id":"prt_e2463a586001o3KYCe7ZtFZ4Bs","sessionID":"ses_1db9e25c4ffeWL056lNnlwtuko","messageID":"msg_e2461da79001U4QE1Fh0EENbxB"}}
