{"type":"text","timestamp":1778723311482,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3ba8ffe35GrghU06hsjLg","part":{"id":"prt_e242bc5570015A2Ik4pMCPOWLw","messageID":"msg_e242baf2e0016K65ZnjkrCkM82","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3ba8ffe35GrghU06hsjLg","type":"text","text":"The hypothesis file has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml`\n\nIt proposes adding a static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken) to the IF stage. This structural change eliminates the 1-cycle bubble for the most common taken branches with minimal LUT overhead, targeting an ~8% IPC improvement for CoreMark loops.","time":{"start":1778723308887,"end":1778723311481}}}
