{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778724811588,"sessionID":"ses_1dbbd8558ffeBxliGckE4NqTl7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"head -n 5 cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl && echo \"---\" && tail -n 20 cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","description":"Check recent experiment log entries"},"output":"{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4217612\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:36:12.712654Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"schema_error: while scanning a simple key\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 6, column 1\\ncould not find expected ':'\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 7, column 1\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 1}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Insert decode-and-predict logic in the IF stage. When the fetched instruction is\\na BRANCH with a negative immediate (backward loop) or an unconditional JAL, the\\nPC is updated to the computed target instead of PC+4. A 1-bit pred_taken flag is\\nthreaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. The EX stage suppresses redirect\\nwhen the prediction was correct; it only asserts redirect (triggering IF/ID flush)\\non mispredict. JALR remains unpredicted. This saves one cycle per correctly\\npredicted taken branch or JAL.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 324.08, \"delta_pct\": 14.59, \"vs_baseline\": 14.59, \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10189, \"ff\": 1874, \"seeds\": [133.46, 138.05, 148.35], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:11:08.300480Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 1, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r1s1 (improvement, +14.59%): Even a trivial static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken) eliminates the taken-branch bubble and yields double-digit IPC gains on loop-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark, with negligible LUT cost.\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction in ID stage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:01:33.428670Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1}\n---\n{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4217612\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:36:12.712654Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"schema_error: while scanning a simple key\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 6, column 1\\ncould not find expected ':'\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 7, column 1\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 1}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Insert decode-and-predict logic in the IF stage. When the fetched instruction is\\na BRANCH with a negative immediate (backward loop) or an unconditional JAL, the\\nPC is updated to the computed target instead of PC+4. A 1-bit pred_taken flag is\\nthreaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. The EX stage suppresses redirect\\nwhen the prediction was correct; it only asserts redirect (triggering IF/ID flush)\\non mispredict. JALR remains unpredicted. This saves one cycle per correctly\\npredicted taken branch or JAL.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 324.08, \"delta_pct\": 14.59, \"vs_baseline\": 14.59, \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05, \"ipc_corem