anch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:01:33.428670Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1}\n---\n{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4217612\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:36:12.712654Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"schema_error: while scanning a simple key\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 6, column 1\\ncould not find expected ':'\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 7, column 1\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 1}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Insert decode-and-predict logic in the IF stage. When the fetched instruction is\\na BRANCH with a negative immediate (backward loop) or an unconditional JAL, the\\nPC is updated to the computed target instead of PC+4. A 1-bit pred_taken flag is\\nthreaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. The EX stage suppresses redirect\\nwhen the prediction was correct; it only asserts redirect (triggering IF/ID flush)\\non mispredict. JALR remains unpredicted. This saves one cycle per correctly\\npredicted taken branch or JAL.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"}], \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 324.08, \"delta_pct\": 14.59, \"vs_baseline\": 14.59, \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10189, \"ff\": 1874, \"seeds\": [133.46, 138.05, 148.35], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:11:08.300480Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 1, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-2