{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778722994613,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c0effeqgIXHYIFsQ61A1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\ntitle: Static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction in ID stage\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\n  fixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\n  loop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\n  Backward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\n  prediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\n  most common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\n  1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\n  2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\n  3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\n     the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\n     EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\n     predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\n     target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\n   (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\n  \n  This turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\n  and unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\n  JALR at their existing penalties.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 10\n  confidence: high\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\n      outputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\n      assert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\n      and capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\n      but below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\n      `predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\n      mispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\n      predicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\n      logic untouched.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\n      `if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\n      No top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778722994595,"end":1778722994611}},"id":"prt_e2426b04b00155NXodmXTGUzOF","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c0effeqgIXHYIFsQ61A1","messageID":"msg_e2426644f001LyB61hgDOMuTGV"}}
