{"type":"text","timestamp":1778723011605,"sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c0effeqgIXHYIFsQ61A1","part":{"id":"prt_e242726b2001jA4V5TWKVY71s0","messageID":"msg_e242712390017tInvMwoItstIJ","sessionID":"ses_1dbdf3c0effeqgIXHYIFsQ61A1","type":"text","text":"Done. The hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Proposed a **static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction** for the 5-stage `cores/bench` pipeline.\n\n- **Why:** The current core pays a 2-cycle bubble on every taken branch and every jump because PC+4 is always fetched and EX-stage redirect flushes IF/ID. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward branches are taken most of the time.\n- **What:** In ID stage, predict JAL as always-taken and conditional branches as taken if their immediate is negative (backward). Redirect IF and flush the combinational IF/ID output immediately. Carry a `predict_taken` bit through ID/EX so EX only asserts `redirect` on a true mispredict. JALR is deliberately *not* predicted to avoid using a potentially stale `rs1` value.\n- **Expected impact:** ~10% fitness improvement (higher IPC from eliminated bubbles) with minimal area/Fmax risk. Confidence: **high**.","time":{"start":1778723006130,"end":1778723011601}}}
