D stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778724811773,"end":1778724811784}},"id":"prt_e2442b241001koqLPlwhLQAIBQ","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","messageID":"msg_e24427a7d001wNIbMA3YKhAXHu"}}
