{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778725101926,"sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep '\"predictor\"' /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","description":"Find predictor category entries in bench log"},"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction in ID stage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:01:33.428670Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction in ID stage\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 10, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:01:33.428670Z\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 1}\n","exit":0,"description":"Find predictor category entries in bench log","truncated":false},"title":"Find predictor category entries in bench log","time":{"start":1778725101921,"end":1778725101925}},"id":"prt_e24471ae6001DMjGI2Msdh8a8M","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","messageID":"msg_e24470c9a0022QpkZH8e9vuNut"}}
