{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778725145300,"sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\ntitle: \"Add 4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR return prediction\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\n  unconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\n  flush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\n  nested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\n  instruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\n  address on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\n  return target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\n  instruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\n  fetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\n  pop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\n  pred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\n  ID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\n  redirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\n  differs from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\n  non-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\n  returns.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778725145285,"end":1778725145299}},"id":"prt_e24479384001zaC7TAMM8t70dd","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","messageID":"msg_e24478504001EdQgYfLIlHsgI0"}}
