s_delta_pct: 3\n25:   confidence: medium\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n28:     description: \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n32:     description: \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n34:     description: \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\ntitle: \"Add 4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR return prediction\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\n  unconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\n  flush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\n  nested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\n  instruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\n  address on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\n  return target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\n  instruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\n  fetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\n  pop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\n  pred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\n  ID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\n  redirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\n  differs from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778725153525,"end":1778725153536}},"id":"prt_e2447e5e6001HfyLGvUdd1jf3q","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","messageID":"msg_e2447ccf4001wZimzAkBoTysop"}}
