{"type":"text","timestamp":1778725165326,"sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","part":{"id":"prt_e24480c7a001KQkMO3S5duFuab","messageID":"msg_e2447ec700011xP6f7W1O6Ze7j","sessionID":"ses_1dbbd85c1ffeWxVRBKN399mdWE","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Proposes adding a 4-entry Return Address Stack (RAS) to the IF-stage predictor. The RAS pushes PC+4 on JAL-to-link-register (x1/x5) and pops the top entry on JALR-from-link-register, predicting return targets in IF. The predicted target is threaded through `if_id_t`/`id_ex_t` so EX can verify it and only redirect on mispredict. This targets the remaining 1-cycle bubble on function returns, which the existing static predictor does not cover. Expected fitness delta: +3% (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778725162106,"end":1778725165324}}}
