-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0/formal/last_run-63200.log\\nPer-check logs in: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0/formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench-63200/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 7,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Consolidate ALU multipliers to reduce routing congestion and improve Fmax\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current ALU unconditionally computes three separate 64-bit products\\n(mul_ss, mul_uu, mul_su) on every cycle even though only one multiply\\nop is ever active.  On FPGA this causes the synthesis tool to infer\\nmultiple wide multipliers and large cross-products that consume DSP\\nblocks and routing resources around the EX stage.  CoreMark is\\nmultiply-heavy (matrix operations), so the ALU multiplier path is\\nlikely on or near the critical path.  By sharing a single 64-bit\\nmultiplier and selecting the signedness mode per-op, we cut the\\nmultiplier area by roughly two thirds and relieve routing\\ncongestion, which should raise median Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current ALU unconditionally computes three separate 64-bit products\\n(mul_ss, mul_uu, mul_su) on every cycle even though only one multiply\\nop is ever active.  On FPGA this causes the synthesis tool to infer\\nmultiple wide multipliers and large cross-products that consume DSP\\nblocks and routing resources around the EX stage.  CoreMark is\\nmultiply-heavy (matrix operations), so the ALU multiplier path is\\nlikely on or near the critical path.  By sharing a single 64-bit\\nmultiplier and selecting the signedness mode per-op, we cut the\\nmultiplier area by roughly two thirds and relieve routing\\ncongestion, which should raise median Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the three always-computed 64-bit products in alu.sv with one\\nshared 64-bit multiplier whose operands are muxed per the active ALU\\nop: unsigned*unsigned for MUL/MULHU, signed*signed for MULH, and\\nsigned*unsigned for MULHSU.  Add a small case block before the\\nmultiplication that selects the correctly-extended a and b inputs.\\nThe DIV/REM family remains combinational (unchanged); only the MUL\\nfamily is touched.  This reduces inferred multiplier count from three\\nto one, shrinking EX-stage area and easing nextpnr placement.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove the three always-on 64-bit product wires (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su).  Add a shared 64-bit `mul_result` wire.  Precede the\\nmultiply with a combinational mux that selects the sign-extended\\noperands based on the current ALU op, then assign mul_result once.\\nUpdate the MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU case arms to pick the correct\\nhigh or low half of mul_result.  Keep the ALTOPS branch intact.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove the three always-on 64-bit product wires (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su).  Add a shared 64-bit `mul_result` wire.  Precede the\\nmultiply with a combinational mux that selects the sign-extended\\noperands based on the current ALU op, then assign mul_result once.\\nUpdate the MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU case arms to pick the correct\\nhigh or low half of mul_result.  Keep the ALTOPS branch intact.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 347.76,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 22.96,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10254,\n  \"ff\": 1940,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.18,\n    132.82,\n    146.26\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:38:10.504767Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 8\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Word-load bypass from MEM to EX stage\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"Prior MEM-to-EX load bypass failed because the critical path through\\nvariable-shift + sign-extend degraded Fmax enough to cancel IPC gains.\\nWord loads (LW) are the dominant load type in CoreMark pointer chasing\\nand need no byte-alignment or sign-extension. A bypass that forwards\\nraw dmem_rdata straight from MEM to EX for LW-only dependencies keeps\\nthe bypass wire path very short, potentially recovering the IPC gain\\nwithout the Fmax loss that killed the full-width bypass.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"Prior MEM-to-EX load bypass failed because the critical path through\\nvariable-shift + sign-extend degraded Fmax enough to cancel IPC gains.\\nWord loads (LW) are the dominant load type in CoreMark pointer chasing\\nand need no byte-alignment or sign-extension. A bypass that forwards\\nraw dmem_rdata straight from MEM to EX for LW-only dependencies keeps\\nthe bypass wire path very short, potentially recovering the IPC gain\\nwithout the Fmax loss that killed the full-width bypass.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a fast MEM-to-EX forwarding path for word loads only: when a LW is\\nin MEM and the instruction in EX reads its rd, forward io_dmemRData\\ndirectly into the EX operand muxes (encoding 2'd3). Suppress the\\nload-use stall in hazard_unit when the load in EX is a word load\\n(mem_width == 2'd2), so the dependent instruction reaches EX in the\\ncycle the LW is in MEM. Keep the existing 1-cycle stall for byte and\\nhalfword loads. Extend forward_unit to prioritise the new dmem bypass\\nover EX/MEM forwarding when active.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Route io_dmemRData into ex_stage as fwd_dmem_rdata. Compute fwd_dmem_en from ex_mem_w (mem_read && mem_width==word && rd!=0) and feed it to both forward_unit and ex_stage.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add id_ex_mem_width input. Suppress load_use_hazard when id_ex_mem_width == 2'd2 (word load) so the stall is only inserted for byte/halfword loads.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_dmem_en input. Prioritise dmem bypass (2'd3) over normal EX/MEM forwarding when a word load sits in MEM and its rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_dmem_rdata and fwd_dmem_en inputs. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_dmem_rdata for select code 2'd3.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Route io_dmemRData into ex_stage as fwd_dmem_rdata. Compute fwd_dmem_en from ex_mem_w (mem_read && mem_width==word && rd!=0) and feed it to both forward_unit and ex_stage.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add id_ex_mem_width input. Suppress load_use_hazard when id_ex_mem_width == 2'd2 (word load) so the stall is only inserted for byte/halfword loads.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add fwd_dmem_en input. Prioritise dmem bypass (2'd3) over normal EX/MEM forwarding when a word load sits in MEM and its rd matches the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add fwd_dmem_rdata and fwd_dmem_en inputs. Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_dmem_rdata for select code 2'd3.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 347.76,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 22.96,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10254,\n  \"ff\": 1940,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.18,\n    132.82,\n    146.26\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T07:06:41.666406Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 9,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv']\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r6s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Fold WB mux into MEM stage and remove dead EX/MEM fields\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The MEM/WB->EX forwarding path currently includes the combinational WB-stage\\nmux (mem_to_reg ? read_data : alu_result). Because fwd_mem_wb is driven by\\nwb_w_data, every instruction that forwards from MEM/WB pays the delay of this\\n32-bit 2:1 mux on top of the MEM/WB register Q, forwarding comparison, and\\nEX operand mux.  On a low-end FPGA this extra mux depth can be the difference\\nbetween timing closure and a slight Fmax loss.  Additionally, ex_mem_t carries\\nbranch_taken and branch_target fields that are written in EX but never read\\ndownstream, wasting ~33 flops.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The MEM/WB->EX forwarding path currently includes the combinational WB-stage\\nmux (mem_to_reg ? read_data : alu_result). Because fwd_mem_wb is driven by\\nwb_w_data, every instruction that forwards from MEM/WB pays the delay of this\\n32-bit 2:1 mux on top of the MEM/WB register Q, forwarding comparison, and\\nEX operand mux.  On a low-end FPGA this extra mux depth can be the difference\\nbetween timing closure and a slight Fmax loss.  Additionally, ex_mem_t carries\\nbranch_taken and branch_target fields that are written in EX but never read\\ndownstream, wasting ~33 flops.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Move the write-back data selection into the MEM stage so that the MEM/WB\\nregister stores only the final rd_wdata (already muxed between load_data and\\nalu_result).  The WB stage then becomes a pure passthrough.  This removes one\\n32-bit mux from the MEM/WB->EX forwarding critical path.  At the same time,\\ndelete the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t to\\nreduce area and routing congestion.  No pipeline behaviour changes; IPC stays\\nidentical and Fmax should improve slightly.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove branch_taken and branch_target from ex_mem_t (dead fields).\\nReplace alu_result and read_data in mem_wb_t with a single rd_wdata\\nfield that holds the final register write data.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Stop writing branch_taken and branch_target into the EX/MEM register.\\nAll other fields remain unchanged.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Compute rd_wdata = in.ctrl.mem_to_reg ? load_data : in.alu_result\\ncombinationally and store it in the MEM/WB register as reg_q.rd_wdata.\\nRemove the now-redundant alu_result and read_data assignments.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/wb_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace the mem_to_reg mux with a passthrough: w_data = in.rd_wdata.\\nw_en and w_addr logic stays identical.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove branch_taken and branch_target from ex_mem_t (dead fields).\\nReplace alu_result and read_data in mem_wb_t with a single rd_wdata\\nfield that holds the final register write data.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Stop writing branch_taken and branch_target into the EX/MEM register.\\nAll other fields remain unchanged.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Compute rd_wdata = in.ctrl.mem_to_reg ? load_data : in.alu_result\\ncombinationally and store it in the MEM/WB register as reg_q.rd_wdata.\\nRemove the now-redundant alu_result and read_data assignments.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/wb_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace the mem_to_reg mux with a passthrough: w_data = in.rd_wdata.\\nw_en and w_addr logic stays identical.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 229.88,\n  \"delta_pct\": -33.9,\n  \"vs_baseline\": -18.72,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 96.63,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10222,\n  \"ff\": 1915,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    99.71,\n    96.63,\n    92.38\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T04:50:14.606389Z\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 6,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r7s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Precompute forwarding selects in ID stage to shorten EX critical path\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The EX-stage critical path currently includes the forward_unit's 5-bit\\naddress comparison, priority encoder, and operand forwarding mux before the\\nALU.  On a LUT-based FPGA these extra logic levels consume precious\\nnanoseconds.  By shifting the forwarding decision into the ID stage\\u2014where\\nthe same comparison is performed against the instructions currently in EX\\nand MEM\\u2014we register the 2-bit select signals into the ID/EX pipeline\\nregister.  This removes the comparison and control generation from the\\nEX-stage datapath without changing pipeline behaviour or IPC.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The EX-stage critical path currently includes the forward_unit's 5-bit\\naddress comparison, priority encoder, and operand forwarding mux before the\\nALU.  On a LUT-based FPGA these extra logic levels consume precious\\nnanoseconds.  By shifting the forwarding decision into the ID stage\\u2014where\\nthe same comparison is performed against the instructions currently in EX\\nand MEM\\u2014we register the 2-bit select signals into the ID/EX pipeline\\nregister.  This removes the comparison and control generation from the\\nEX-stage datapath without changing pipeline behaviour or IPC.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add fwd_rs1_sel and fwd_rs2_sel (2 bits each) to the id_ex_t bundle.\\nIn id_stage, compute the forwarding selects combinationally by comparing\\nthe current IF/ID instruction's rs1_addr/rs2_addr against the rd and\\nreg_write flags of the instruction currently in EX (the ID/EX register)\\nand the instruction currently in MEM (ex_mem_w), preserving the same\\nEX/MEM-over-MEM/WB priority and x0 guard that forward_unit uses today.\\nRegister these selects into the ID/EX payload.  In ex_stage, remove the\\nforward_unit input ports and use the precomputed in.fwd_rs1_sel /\\nin.fwd_rs2_sel directly in the operand forwarding muxes.  In core.sv,\\nwire ex_mem_w.rd and ex_mem_w.ctrl.reg_write into id_stage for the\\nprecomputation, remove the forward_unit instantiation, and connect the\\nprecomputed selects straight through to ex_stage.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add fwd_rs1_sel [1:0] and fwd_rs2_sel [1:0] fields to the id_ex_t struct.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add inputs ex_mem_rd [4:0] and ex_mem_reg_write. Compute next_fwd_rs1/next_fwd_rs2 combinationally by comparing in.instr[19:15] and in.instr[24:20] against reg_q.rd and ex_mem_rd with the same write-enable / x0 guards used by forward_unit. Register the resulting 2-bit values into the ID/EX payload.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Remove the fwd_rs1_sel and fwd_rs2_sel input ports. Use in.fwd_rs1_sel and in.fwd_rs2_sel directly in the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes instead of the former forward_unit-driven selects.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire ex_mem_w.rd and ex_mem_w.ctrl.reg_write into the id_stage instance for precomputation.  Remove the forward_unit instantiation and its wires.  Connect id_ex_w.fwd_rs1_sel and id_ex_w.fwd_rs2_sel directly to ex_stage.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add fwd_rs1_sel [1:0] and fwd_rs2_sel [1:0] fields to the id_ex_t struct.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add inputs ex_mem_rd [4:0] and ex_mem_reg_write. Compute next_fwd_rs1/next_fwd_rs2 combinationally by comparing in.instr[19:15] and in.instr[24:20] against reg_q.rd and ex_mem_rd with the same write-enable / x0 guards used by forward_unit. Register the resulting 2-bit values into the ID/EX payload.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Remove the fwd_rs1_sel and fwd_rs2_sel input ports. Use in.fwd_rs1_sel and in.fwd_rs2_sel directly in the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes instead of the former forward_unit-driven selects.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire ex_mem_w.rd and ex_mem_w.ctrl.reg_write into the id_stage instance for precomputation.  Remove the forward_unit instantiation and its wires.  Connect id_ex_w.fwd_rs1_sel and id_ex_w.fwd_rs2_sel directly to ex_stage.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"formal_failed: reg_ch0\\n: pass\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_sw_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_sw_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Checking assertions in step 20..\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Status: passed\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] engine_0: finished (returncode=0)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] engine_0: Status returned by engine: pass\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: Elapsed clock time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:00 (0)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: Elapsed process time [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:01 (1)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned pass\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] summary: engine_0 did not produce any traces\\nSBY  2:58:03 [insn_xori_ch0] DONE (PASS, rc=0)\\n\\nFormal: 52 passed, 1 failed\\nFailed: reg_ch0\\n\\n--- reg_ch0/logfile.txt (last 30 lines) ---\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 9..\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 10..\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 11..\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 12..\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] engine_0: ##   0:00:00  Skipping step 13..\\nSBY  2:57:53 [reg_ch0] eng