{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778729188178,"sessionID":"ses_1db8046f7ffea7R3cj6vyORNkk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"grep:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"micro_opt","path":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments","include":"*.jsonl"},"output":"Found 4 matches\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\n  Line 1: {\"id\": \"baseline-bench-4217612\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T01:36:12.712654Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n\n  Line 2: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"schema_error: while scanning a simple key\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 6, column 1\\ncould not find expected ':'\\n  in \\\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\\\", line 7, column 1\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 1}\n\n  Line 5: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\", \"title\": \"MEM-to-EX load bypass to eliminate load-use stalls\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause it can only forward loaded data from MEM/WB, not from the MEM stage\\nitself.  CoreMark pointer-chasing and array-index patterns frequently emit a\\nLOAD followed immediately by a dependent ALU or STORE.  Eliminating the\\nload-use bubble improves IPC with no extra pipeline stages or tables.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause it can only forward loaded data from MEM/WB, not from the MEM stage\\nitself.  CoreMark pointer-chasing and array-index patterns frequently emit a\\nLOAD followed immediately by a dependent ALU or STORE.  Eliminating the\\nload-use bubble improves IPC with no extra pipeline stages or tables.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational bypass from mem_stage's load_data output back to the\\nEX-stage operand muxes.  Extend the forwarding_unit so that when EX/MEM\\ncontains a LOAD whose rd matches an EX-stage rs, it selects the new bypass\\npath (encoding 2'b11).  Remove the load_use_hazard stall from hazard_unit;\\nthe bypass makes it unnecessary.  All other stalls (imem/dmem backpressure,\\nredirect flush) remain unchanged.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. The MEM\\u2192EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_mem_load ...\n  Line 8: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Eliminate false load-use stalls via opcode-aware hazard detection\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add opcode decoding to hazard_unit so load-use detection only fires when\\nthe instruction in ID actually reads rs1/rs2 as registers. R-type, I-type\\n(OP-IMM/LOAD/JALR), S-type, and B-type use rs1; R-type, S-type, and B-type\\nuse rs2. U-type and J-type use neither. This removes false stalls without\\naltering pipeline structure or lengthening critical paths.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": ...","metadata":{"matches":4,"truncated":false},"title":"micro_opt","time":{"start":1778729188164,"end":1778729188177}},"id":"prt_e24857779001GBa0GklTaa64Ms","sessionID":"ses_1db8046f7ffea7R3cj6vyORNkk","messageID":"msg_e247fb94a001HSGePtc6WY9lte"}}
