ot from the MEM stage\\nitself.  CoreMark pointer-chasing and array-index patterns frequently emit a\\nLOAD followed immediately by a dependent ALU or STORE.  Eliminating the\\nload-use bubble improves IPC with no extra pipeline stages or tables.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline stalls for one cycle on every load-use hazard\\nbecause it can only forward loaded data from MEM/WB, not from the MEM stage\\nitself.  CoreMark pointer-chasing and array-index patterns frequently emit a\\nLOAD followed immediately by a dependent ALU or STORE.  Eliminating the\\nload-use bubble improves IPC with no extra pipeline stages or tables.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a combinational bypass from mem_stage's load_data output back to the\\nEX-stage operand muxes.  Extend the forwarding_unit so that when EX/MEM\\ncontains a LOAD whose rd matches an EX-stage rs, it selects the new bypass\\npath (encoding 2'b11).  Remove the load_use_hazard stall from hazard_unit;\\nthe bypass makes it unnecessary.  All other stalls (imem/dmem backpressure,\\nredirect flush) remain unchanged.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. The MEM\\u2192EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_mem_load when the forwarding select is 2'b11.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data signal as a new output port load_data_fwd [31:0] so core.sv can route it back to ex_stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire mem_stage.load_data_fwd to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load.  Connect ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.  Update the hazard_unit instantiation to reflect removed load-use stall logic.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. The MEM\\u2192EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_mem_load when the forwarding select is 2'b11.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data signal as a new output port load_data_fwd [31:0] so core.sv can route it back to ex_stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire mem_stage.load_data_fwd to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load.  Connect ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.  Update the hazard_unit instantiation to reflect removed load-use stall logic.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 324.08, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 14.59, \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10189, \"ff\": 1874, \"seeds\": [133.46, 138.05, 148.35], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:41:03.769480Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/test/test_pip