ect flush) remain unchanged.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. The MEM\\u2192EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_mem_load when the forwarding select is 2'b11.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data signal as a new output port load_data_fwd [31:0] so core.sv can route it back to ex_stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire mem_stage.load_data_fwd to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load.  Connect ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.  Update the hazard_unit instantiation to reflect removed load-use stall logic.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 7, \"confidence\": \"high\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the load_use_hazard term from stall_if, stall_id, and flush_id. The MEM\\u2192EX bypass eliminates the need to stall the pipeline for load-use.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add ex_mem_mem_read input.  When EX/MEM has a matching rd and ex_mem_mem_read is high, drive fwd_rs1/fwd_rs2 = 2'b11 to select the MEM-stage load bypass instead of the ALU-result path.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add fwd_mem_load [31:0] input.  Extend the rs1/rs2 forwarding muxes to select fwd_mem_load when the forwarding select is 2'b11.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Expose the combinational load_data signal as a new output port load_data_fwd [31:0] so core.sv can route it back to ex_stage.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire mem_stage.load_data_fwd to ex_stage.fwd_mem_load.  Connect ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_mem_read.  Update the hazard_unit instantiation to reflect removed load-use stall logic.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 324.08, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 14.59, \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4259699, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10189, \"ff\": 1874, \"seeds\": [133.46, 138.05, 148.35], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:41:03.769480Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 2, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/test/test_pipeline.py']\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Eliminate false load-use stalls via opcode-aware hazard detection\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add opcode decoding to hazard_unit so load-use detection only fires when\\nthe instruction in ID actually reads rs1/rs2 as registers. R-type, I-type\\n(OP-IMM/LOAD/JALR), S-type, and B-type use rs1; R-type, S-type, and B-type\\nuse rs2. U-type and J-type use neither. This removes false stalls without\\naltering pipeline structure or lengthening critical paths.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add opcode input and uses_rs1/uses_rs2 qualification to the load_use_hazard check.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire if_id_w.instr[6:0] to the hazard_unit's new opcode input.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add opcode input and uses_rs1/uses_rs2 qualification to the load_use_hazard check.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire if_id_w.instr[6:0] to the hazard_unit's new opcode input.\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"cosim_failed: selftest.elf\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 3, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r4s0\", \"title\": \"(slot 0 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-001-r4s0 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r4s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r4s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r4s2'])\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 4}\n","exit":0,"description":"Grep micro_opt hypotheses from log","truncated":false},"title":"Grep micro_opt hypotheses from log","time":{"start":1778731659497,"end":1778731659500}},"id":"prt_e24ab2ca7001ktPW4HHLUfgxSp","sessionID":"ses_1db556a4affe7hShpYdghPERa0","messageID":"msg_e24aa95f0001w0sei7bpDYcizz"}}
