{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778732094493,"sessionID":"ses_1db556a4affe7hShpYdghPERa0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r5s0\ntitle: Eliminate false load-use stalls via opcode-aware hazard detection\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The hazard_unit conservatively stalls on any LOAD-to-use sequence where the\n  LOAD's rd matches either rs1 or rs2 of the next instruction, regardless of\n  whether those fields are actually register reads. For I-type instructions\n  (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR) the rs2 field encodes an immediate or shamt; for U-type\n  (LUI, AUIPC), J-type (JAL), and SYSTEM/FENCE instructions neither field is a\n  register read. These false stalls waste cycles—especially on CoreMark's heavy\n  use of ADDI, LUI, and JAL immediately after pointer loads—with negligible\n  LUT cost and no impact on Fmax.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add opcode decoding to hazard_unit so the load_use_hazard term only fires\n  when the instruction in ID genuinely reads rs1 or rs2. R-type, BRANCH, and\n  STORE read both; I-type reads only rs1; U/J/FENCE/SYSTEM read neither. The\n  stall_if / stall_id / flush_id logic otherwise stays identical, so no other\n  pipeline behavior changes. This removes spurious one-cycle bubbles without\n  lengthening any critical path.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Add a new 7-bit `if_id_opcode` input. Inside the module compute\n      `uses_rs1` and `uses_rs2` flags from the opcode (R/BRANCH/STORE = both;\n      I-type = rs1 only; U/J/FENCE/SYSTEM = neither). Qualify the\n      `load_use_hazard` expression with these flags so that matches on\n      immediate fields no longer stall the pipeline.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Wire `if_id_w.instr[6:0]` into the new `if_id_opcode` port of the\n      `hazard_unit` instance. No other top-level signals are modified.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r5s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778732094490,"end":1778732094493}},"id":"prt_e24b1b53f001kgY8KtgyBAdtgY","sessionID":"ses_1db556a4affe7hShpYdghPERa0","messageID":"msg_e24ac91cf001J18dK5r3x2f25J"}}
