{"type":"text","timestamp":1778733668550,"sessionID":"ses_1db419843ffeQUi9B9VyBNpPkX","part":{"id":"prt_e24c9d14d0019Dz8YoU1lhBnFy","messageID":"msg_e24c9ba64001Ta5uGWyo1tRrMA","sessionID":"ses_1db419843ffeQUi9B9VyBNpPkX","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r6s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Fold the WB-stage `mem_to_reg` mux into the MEM stage so the MEM/WB register stores only the final `rd_wdata`, and delete the unused `branch_taken`/`branch_target` fields from EX/MEM. This removes one 32-bit 2:1 mux from the MEM/WB→EX forwarding critical path and saves ~65 flops, giving a small Fmax boost with zero IPC risk. Expected fitness delta: **+4%** (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778733666637,"end":1778733668548}}}
