{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778736433288,"sessionID":"ses_1db13f4edffe6UBI9bfWCBljE1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r7s0\ntitle: Precompute forwarding selects in ID stage to shorten EX critical path\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX-stage critical path currently includes the forward_unit's 5-bit\n  address comparison, priority encoder, and operand forwarding mux before the\n  ALU.  On a LUT-based FPGA these extra logic levels consume precious\n  nanoseconds.  By shifting the forwarding decision into the ID stage—where\n  the same comparison is performed against the instructions currently in EX\n  and MEM—we register the 2-bit select signals into the ID/EX pipeline\n  register.  This removes the comparison and control generation from the\n  EX-stage datapath without changing pipeline behaviour or IPC.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add fwd_rs1_sel and fwd_rs2_sel (2 bits each) to the id_ex_t bundle.\n  In id_stage, compute the forwarding selects combinationally by comparing\n  the current IF/ID instruction's rs1_addr/rs2_addr against the rd and\n  reg_write flags of the instruction currently in EX (the ID/EX register)\n  and the instruction currently in MEM (ex_mem_w), preserving the same\n  EX/MEM-over-MEM/WB priority and x0 guard that forward_unit uses today.\n  Register these selects into the ID/EX payload.  In ex_stage, remove the\n  forward_unit input ports and use the precomputed in.fwd_rs1_sel /\n  in.fwd_rs2_sel directly in the operand forwarding muxes.  In core.sv,\n  wire ex_mem_w.rd and ex_mem_w.ctrl.reg_write into id_stage for the\n  precomputation, remove the forward_unit instantiation, and connect the\n  precomputed selects straight through to ex_stage.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: Add fwd_rs1_sel [1:0] and fwd_rs2_sel [1:0] fields to the id_ex_t struct.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add inputs ex_mem_rd [4:0] and ex_mem_reg_write.\n      Compute next_fwd_rs1/next_fwd_rs2 combinationally by comparing\n      in.instr[19:15] and in.instr[24:20] against reg_q.rd and ex_mem_rd\n      with the same write-enable / x0 guards used by forward_unit.\n      Register the resulting 2-bit values into the ID/EX payload.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Remove the fwd_rs1_sel and fwd_rs2_sel input ports.\n      Use in.fwd_rs1_sel and in.fwd_rs2_sel directly in the rs1/rs2\n      forwarding muxes instead of the former forward_unit-driven selects.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Wire ex_mem_w.rd and ex_mem_w.ctrl.reg_write into the id_stage\n      instance for precomputation.  Remove the forward_unit instantiation\n      and its wires.  Connect id_ex_w.fwd_rs1_sel and id_ex_w.fwd_rs2_sel\n      directly to ex_stage.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778736433273,"end":1778736433287}},"id":"prt_e24f3e194001oXp9VLB3ks90yk","sessionID":"ses_1db13f4edffe6UBI9bfWCBljE1","messageID":"msg_e24f3d155001KcfumtjypNKSzE"}}
