{"type":"text","timestamp":1778736445585,"sessionID":"ses_1db13f4edffe6UBI9bfWCBljE1","part":{"id":"prt_e24f42e8d0017KzhrxludPbNL5","messageID":"msg_e24f41e74002H0X4Qnd1hKdvRk","sessionID":"ses_1db13f4edffe6UBI9bfWCBljE1","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis YAML written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of the proposed micro-opt:**  \nPrecompute the forwarding select bits (`fwd_rs1_sel` / `fwd_rs2_sel`) in the ID stage rather than in the EX stage. By comparing the instruction currently in ID against the writers in EX and MEM one cycle earlier, the 2-bit mux controls can be registered into the `ID/EX` pipeline register. This strips the address-comparison and priority-encoder logic out of the EX-stage critical path (between the pipeline registers and the ALU), potentially improving Fmax without altering IPC or pipeline behaviour.","time":{"start":1778736443021,"end":1778736445583}}}
