{"type":"text","timestamp":1778740089677,"sessionID":"ses_1dadf92e0ffeJugLoyJPf403ih","part":{"id":"prt_e252bc891001d2yWVbtZimJa45","messageID":"msg_e252bc079001qlQqkkbXtXVGH4","sessionID":"ses_1dadf92e0ffeJugLoyJPf403ih","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to:\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r8s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** `micro_opt`\n- **Idea:** Consolidate the ALU's three separate 64-bit multipliers (`mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, `mul_su`) into a single shared 64-bit multiplier with sign-mode muxing per instruction.\n- **Rationale:** The current ALU unconditionally computes all three products every cycle, causing the FPGA toolchain to infer multiple wide multipliers that consume DSP blocks and congest routing around the EX stage. CoreMark is multiply-heavy, so reducing multiplier area by ~2/3 should improve median Fmax with zero IPC impact.\n- **Expected impact:** +3% fitness, medium confidence.","time":{"start":1778740086929,"end":1778740089674}}}
