{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778741609121,"sessionID":"ses_1dac84e57ffeCHEwIvN8flv1iG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\ntitle: Word-load bypass from MEM to EX stage\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  Prior MEM-to-EX load bypass failed because the critical path through\n  variable-shift + sign-extend degraded Fmax enough to cancel IPC gains.\n  Word loads (LW) are the dominant load type in CoreMark pointer chasing\n  and need no byte-alignment or sign-extension. A bypass that forwards\n  raw dmem_rdata straight from MEM to EX for LW-only dependencies keeps\n  the bypass wire path very short, potentially recovering the IPC gain\n  without the Fmax loss that killed the full-width bypass.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a fast MEM-to-EX forwarding path for word loads only: when a LW is\n  in MEM and the instruction in EX reads its rd, forward io_dmemRData\n  directly into the EX operand muxes (encoding 2'd3). Suppress the\n  load-use stall in hazard_unit when the load in EX is a word load\n  (mem_width == 2'd2), so the dependent instruction reaches EX in the\n  cycle the LW is in MEM. Keep the existing 1-cycle stall for byte and\n  halfword loads. Extend forward_unit to prioritise the new dmem bypass\n  over EX/MEM forwarding when active.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Route io_dmemRData into ex_stage as fwd_dmem_rdata. Compute\n      fwd_dmem_en from ex_mem_w (mem_read && mem_width==word && rd!=0)\n      and feed it to both forward_unit and ex_stage.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add id_ex_mem_width input. Suppress load_use_hazard when\n      id_ex_mem_width == 2'd2 (word load) so the stall is only inserted\n      for byte/halfword loads.\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: >\n      Add fwd_dmem_en input. Prioritise dmem bypass (2'd3) over normal\n      EX/MEM forwarding when a word load sits in MEM and its rd matches\n      the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add fwd_dmem_rdata and fwd_dmem_en inputs. Extend the rs1/rs2\n      forwarding muxes to select fwd_dmem_rdata for select code 2'd3.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778741609114,"end":1778741609120}},"id":"prt_e2542b101002i2p8rf1HWrT4gz","sessionID":"ses_1dac84e57ffeCHEwIvN8flv1iG","messageID":"msg_e254298b6001O5QhZyPRfCB0fA"}}
