en from ex_mem_w (mem_read && mem_width==word && rd!=0)\n29:       and feed it to both forward_unit and ex_stage.\n30:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n31:     description: >\n32:       Add id_ex_mem_width input. Suppress load_use_hazard when\n33:       id_ex_mem_width == 2'd2 (word load) so the stall is only inserted\n34:       for byte/halfword loads.\n35:   - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n36:     description: >\n37:       Add fwd_dmem_en input. Prioritise dmem bypass (2'd3) over normal\n38:       EX/MEM forwarding when a word load sits in MEM and its rd matches\n39:       the EX-stage rs1/rs2.\n40:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n41:     description: >\n42:       Add fwd_dmem_rdata and fwd_dmem_en inputs. Extend the rs1/rs2\n43:       forwarding muxes to select fwd_dmem_rdata for select code 2'd3.\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260514-001-r9s0\ntitle: Word-load bypass from MEM to EX stage\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  Prior MEM-to-EX load bypass failed because the critical path through\n  variable-shift + sign-extend degraded Fmax enough to cancel IPC gains.\n  Word loads (LW) are the dominant load type in CoreMark pointer chasing\n  and need no byte-alignment or sign-extension. A bypass that forwards\n  raw dmem_rdata straight from MEM to EX for LW-only dependencies keeps\n  the bypass wire path very short, potentially recovering the IPC gain\n  without the Fmax loss that killed the full-width bypass.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a fast MEM-to-EX forwarding path for word loads only: when a LW is\n  in MEM and the instruction in EX reads its rd, forward io_dmemRData\n  directly into the EX operand muxes (encoding 2'd3). Suppress the\n  load-use stall in hazard_unit when the load in EX is a word load\n  (mem_width == 2'd2), so the dependent instruction reaches EX in the\n  cycle the LW is in MEM. Keep the existing 1-cycle stall for byte and\n  halfword loads. Extend forward_unit to prioritise the new dmem bypass\n  over EX/MEM forwarding when active.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778741616730,"end":1778741616734}},"id":"prt_e25431c4c001WAh86KsOvOCe8f","sessionID":"ses_1dac84e57ffeCHEwIvN8flv1iG","messageID":"msg_e25430d1a001sK8leGKo5Zbxc6"}}
