{"type":"text","timestamp":1778741630411,"sessionID":"ses_1dac84e57ffeCHEwIvN8flv1iG","part":{"id":"prt_e25433d8b002HKZpzY6FBwRDLr","messageID":"msg_e25432c65001hezl9TD1PMOGYY","sessionID":"ses_1dac84e57ffeCHEwIvN8flv1iG","type":"text","text":"Done. I wrote the hypothesis file to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-001-r9s0.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the hypothesis:**\n\n- **Category:** `micro_opt`\n- **Core idea:** Add a MEM-to-EX forwarding path **only for word loads (LW)**. The prior full-width MEM-to-EX load bypass failed because the critical path went through variable shift + sign-extend logic, degrading Fmax enough to cancel any IPC gain. LW is the dominant load in CoreMark and requires no byte-alignment or sign-extension, so the bypass path is just `dmem_rdata → EX operand mux`.\n- **Changes:** Modify `core.sv`, `hazard_unit.sv`, `forward_unit.sv`, and `ex_stage.sv` to:\n  1. Suppress the load-use stall when the load in EX is a word (`mem_width == 2'd2`).\n  2. Forward `io_dmemRData` directly to EX when a LW is in MEM and the instruction in EX reads the same `rd`.\n  3. Keep the existing 1-cycle stall for byte/halfword loads.\n- **Expected impact:** `+4%` fitness, `medium` confidence.","time":{"start":1778741624203,"end":1778741630410}}}
