{"type":"text","timestamp":1778745718805,"sessionID":"ses_1da8c0c5bffexq3IwgwBmU1BII","part":{"id":"prt_e25819ffe001NDj6WNEPzjwjVF","messageID":"msg_e258181fe001KazoNhzZrR1sD6","sessionID":"ses_1da8c0c5bffexq3IwgwBmU1BII","type":"text","text":"The hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r11s1.yaml`\n\nIt proposes adding a **1-entry non-blocking store buffer** to decouple store instructions from dmem backpressure. This is a structural change that hides dmem stalls for stores (~5% of cycles) while preserving ordering, with minimal area and no new long combinational paths.","time":{"start":1778745712638,"end":1778745718802}}}
