{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778749905269,"sessionID":"ses_1da496f0affe1xo1ihroyY0XWo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        if d['id'] == 'hyp-20260514-003-r4s2':\n            print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n\"","description":"Extract BHT hypothesis details"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 32-entry 2-bit BHT for forward branch direction prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing IF-stage static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken)\\nalready eliminated the largest source of control bubbles, yielding a +14.6%\\nfitness gain. The remaining dynamic mispredictions come mainly from forward\\nconditional branches that are frequently taken (e.g. early exits, loop-internal\\nconditionals) and from JALR returns. A prior 4-entry RAS improved IPC by only\\n0.3% because returns are rare, while a 32-entry tagged BTB broke in cosim.\\nA saturating-counter BHT attacks the much larger forward-branch bubble source\\nwith minimal area (64 flops) and no changes to pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing IF-stage static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken)\\nalready eliminated the largest source of control bubbles, yielding a +14.6%\\nfitness gain. The remaining dynamic mispredictions come mainly from forward\\nconditional branches that are frequently taken (e.g. early exits, loop-internal\\nconditionals) and from JALR returns. A prior 4-entry RAS improved IPC by only\\n0.3% because returns are rare, while a 32-entry tagged BTB broke in cosim.\\nA saturating-counter BHT attacks the much larger forward-branch bubble source\\nwith minimal area (64 flops) and no changes to pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch History Table with 2-bit saturating\\ncounters to the IF stage. The table is indexed by PC[6:2] and initialized to\\nstrongly-taken (2'b11) so backward loops are correct immediately without any\\ntraining cost. For every conditional branch, the BHT entry MSB drives\\npredict_taken; unconditional JAL continues to be always predicted taken. In\\nEX stage, each resolved branch writes its actual outcome back to the entry\\nindexed by the branch PC using a standard saturating update rule. This adds\\nonly 64 flops and a few LUTs of combinational logic, does not widen any\\npipeline register, and the BHT read is off the critical instruction-fetch path\\nbecause the PC is known at the start of the cycle while the opcode decode\\n(which selects the BHT result) happens later in parallel.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 32-entry x 2-bit BHT array inside the IF stage.  Combinational read uses pc[6:2] to select the counter; the MSB becomes the direction prediction for conditional branches.  Add three new input ports (bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], bht_update_taken) and a saturating update rule that increments on taken and decrements on not-taken.  Modify predict_taken so that conditional branches use the BHT MSB while JAL remains unconditionally taken.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add output ports bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken.  Drive bht_update_en high on every cycle a conditional branch is resolved (!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch). bht_update_idx is in.pc[6:2] and bht_update_taken is the combinational branch_taken signal.  No other EX-stage logic is changed.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken and route them from ex_stage outputs to if_stage inputs. No top-level IO or RVFI changes.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a 32-entry x 2-bit BHT array inside the IF stage.  Combinational read uses pc[6:2] to select the counter; the MSB becomes the direction prediction for conditional branches.  Add three new input ports (bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], bht_update_taken) and a saturating update rule that increments on taken and decrements on not-taken.  Modify predict_taken so that conditional branches use the BHT MSB while JAL remains unconditionally taken.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add output ports bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken.  Drive bht_update_en high on every cycle a conditional branch is resolved (!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch). bht_update_idx is in.pc[6:2] and bht_update_taken is the combinational branch_taken signal.  No other EX-stage logic is changed.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken and route them from ex_stage outputs to if_stage inputs. No top-level IO or RVFI changes.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 347.76,\n  \"delta_pct\": 7.31,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 22.96,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10254,\n  \"ff\": 1940,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.18,\n    132.82,\n    146.26\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:44:01.694682Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 4,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-003-r4s2 (improvement, +7.31%): After a static backward-taken baseline captures the easy loop gains, a minimal 32-entry 2-bit BHT (64 flops) still recovers +7.3% fitness by predicting forward conditional branches; forward-branch direction is the largest remaining dynamic bubble source in CoreMark.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 32-entry 2-bit BHT for forward branch direction prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing IF-stage static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken)\\nalready eliminated the largest source of control bubbles, yielding a +14.6%\\nfitness gain. The remaining dynamic mispredictions come mainly from forward\\nconditional branches that are frequently taken (e.g. early exits, loop-internal\\nconditionals) and from JALR returns. A prior 4-entry RAS improved IPC by only\\n0.3% because returns are rare, while a 32-entry tagged BTB broke in cosim.\\nA saturating-counter BHT attacks the much larger forward-branch bubble source\\nwith minimal area (64 flops) and no changes to pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing IF-stage static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken)\\nalready eliminated the largest source of control bubbles, yielding a +14.6%\\nfitness gain. The remaining dynamic mispredictions come mainly from forward\\nconditional branches that are frequently taken (e.g. early exits, loop-internal\\nconditionals) and from JALR returns. A prior 4-entry RAS improved IPC by only\\n0.3% because returns are rare, while a 32-entry tagged BTB broke in cosim.\\nA saturating-counter BHT attacks the much larger forward-branch bubble source\\nwith minimal area (64 flops) and no changes to pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch History Table with 2-bit saturating\\ncounters to the IF stage. The table is indexed by PC[6:2] and initialized to\\nstrongly-taken (2'b11) so backward loops are correct immediately without any\\ntraining cost. For every conditional branch, the BHT entry MSB drives\\npredict_taken; unconditional JAL continues to be always predicted taken. In\\nEX stage, each resolved branch writes its actual outcome back to the entry\\nindexed by the branch PC using a standard saturating update rule. This adds\\nonly 64 flops and a few LUTs of combinational logic, does not widen any\\npipeline register, and the BHT read is off the critical instruction-fetch path\\nbecause the PC is known at the start of the cycle while the opcode decode\\n(which selects the BHT result) happens later in parallel.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 32-entry x 2-bit BHT array inside the IF stage.  Combinational read uses pc[6:2] to select the counter; the MSB becomes the direction prediction for conditional branches.  Add three new input ports (bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], bht_update_taken) and a saturating update rule that increments on taken and decrements on not-taken.  Modify predict_taken so that conditional branches use the BHT MSB while JAL remains unconditionally taken.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add output ports bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken.  Drive bht_update_en high on every cycle a conditional branch is resolved (!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch). bht_update_idx is in.pc[6:2] and bht_update_taken is the combinational branch_taken signal.  No other EX-stage logic is changed.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken and route them from ex_stage outputs to if_stage inputs. No top-level IO or RVFI changes.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a 32-entry x 2-bit BHT array inside the IF stage.  Combinational read uses pc[6:2] to select the counter; the MSB becomes the direction prediction for conditional branches.  Add three new input ports (bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], bht_update_taken) and a saturating update rule that increments on taken and decrements on not-taken.  Modify predict_taken so that conditional branches use the BHT MSB while JAL remains unconditionally taken.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add output ports bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken.  Drive bht_update_en high on every cycle a conditional branch is resolved (!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch). bht_update_idx is in.pc[6:2] and bht_update_taken is the combinational branch_taken signal.  No other EX-stage logic is changed.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and bht_update_taken and route them from ex_stage outputs to if_stage inputs. No top-level IO or RVFI changes.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 347.76,\n  \"delta_pct\": 7.31,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 22.96,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10254,\n  \"ff\": 1940,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.18,\n    132.82,\n    146.26\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T03:44:01.694682Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 4,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-14 hyp-20260514-003-r4s2 (improvement, +7.31%): After a static backward-taken baseline captures the easy loop gains, a minimal 32-entry 2-bit BHT (64 flops) still recovers +7.3% fitness by predicting forward conditional branches; forward-branch direction is the largest remaining dynamic bubble source in CoreMark.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Extract BHT hypothesis details","truncated":false},"title":"Extract BHT hypothesis details","time":{"start":1778749905265,"end":1778749905269}},"id":"prt_e25c1972a0015DLQkKOEwRg1Be","sessionID":"ses_1da496f0affe1xo1ihroyY0XWo","messageID":"msg_e25bfff98001V1lnG8MK20aHN1"}}
