{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778754360558,"sessionID":"ses_1da08a9b3ffeiE0K02BupWfSfi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep -i 'cache' /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | head -n 10","description":"Search for cache in log"},"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"Add 32-entry tagged BTB with 2-bit saturating counters for branch target caching and forward-branch learning\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch Target Buffer in the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a valid bit, a 5-bit tag (PC[11:7]), a 30-bit\\nword-aligned target, and a 2-bit saturating counter.  In IF, a BTB\\nhit on a branch or JAL supplies the target directly from a register\\nread, bypassing the combinational immediate+adder path.  Direction\\nprediction remains static-taken for backward branches and JAL, but\\nthe BTB can additionally predict taken for forward branches once\\ntheir counter reaches 2.  In EX, every resolved branch/JAL writes\\nits outcome and target back into the BTB.  JALR is excluded from\\nBTB usage to avoid aliasing noise.  This should improve IPC on\\ntaken forward branches and may raise Fmax by reducing IF-stage\\ncombinational delay.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"cosim_failed: coremark.elf\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\", \"title\": \"Add 32-entry tagged BTB with 2-bit saturating counters for branch target caching and forward-branch learning\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch Target Buffer in the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a valid bit, a 5-bit tag (PC[11:7]), a 30-bit\\nword-aligned target, and a 2-bit saturating counter.  In IF, a BTB\\nhit on a branch or JAL supplies the target directly from a register\\nread, bypassing the combinational immediate+adder path.  Direction\\nprediction remains static-taken for backward branches and JAL, but\\nthe BTB can additionally predict taken for forward branches once\\ntheir counter reaches 2.  In EX, every resolved branch/JAL writes\\nits outcome and target back into the BTB.  JALR is excluded from\\nBTB usage to avoid aliasing noise.  This should improve IPC on\\ntaken forward branches and may raise Fmax by reducing IF-stage\\ncombinational delay.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 5, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"cosim_failed: coremark.elf\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 3, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Search for cache in log","truncated":false},"title":"Search for cache in log","time":{"start":1778754360556,"end":1778754360557}},"id":"prt_e2605910b001zbA9JrQ2nHby3c","sessionID":"ses_1da08a9b3ffeiE0K02BupWfSfi","messageID":"msg_e26001e88001a3I504UKpFxapp"}}
