{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778729860851,"sessionID":"ses_1db80468efferIEmTuLHsbaMh6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r4s1\ntitle: \"Move JALR target resolution to ID stage to cut penalty from 2 to 1 cycle\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  JALR is currently unpredicted in IF and resolved in EX, incurring a 2-cycle\n  misprediction bubble on every function return and indirect call. CoreMark's\n  list benchmark makes frequent function calls through pointers, so JALR\n  bubbles are a real IPC limiter.  Because the return address register (x1)\n  is almost always in the regfile when the JALR reaches ID (no forwarding\n  needed), we can compute the target address in ID stage and redirect IF one\n  cycle earlier, shrinking the penalty to a single flushed fetch slot.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a JALR target adder in the ID stage: when the decoded instruction is\n  JALR and its rs1 is not the subject of an in-flight load-use hazard, compute\n  jalr_target = (rs1_data + imm) & ~1 and assert a new id_redirect signal.\n  Thread a jalr_redirected flag through the id_ex_t bundle so the EX stage\n  suppresses its own redirect for JALRs that were already handled in ID.\n  At the top level, OR the new id_redirect with the existing ex_redirect to\n  drive the PC, and adjust flush_if/flush_id so that a JALR in ID is allowed\n  to advance into EX while the speculative fetch in IF is killed.\n  This structural change shortens the JALR resolution loop by one full stage\n  without touching any other instruction type.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add jalr_redirected bit to id_ex_t bundle.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Compute JALR target from regfile rs1 + imm. Assert id_redirect when JALR has no load-use hazard on rs1. Set jalr_redirected flag in the ID/EX register.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Suppress redirect for JALR instructions when jalr_redirected is set; otherwise keep existing redirect logic unchanged.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Add id_redirect input to flush_if logic. Ensure load-use hazard on JALR rs1 stalls ID (do not assert id_redirect until hazard clears).\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire new id_redirect from id_stage to hazard_unit and PC logic. Combine id_redirect with ex_redirect for top-level redirect and flush control.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r4s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778729860832,"end":1778729860849}},"id":"prt_e248f67f10013kFmHYGplKRy65","sessionID":"ses_1db80468efferIEmTuLHsbaMh6","messageID":"msg_e248a836e001g8LxTeMGuJQzEK"}}
