\n26:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n27:     description: |\n28:       Add 1-entry prefetch buffer registers and rewrite the issue / fill\n29:       FSM so that fetch_pc advances on every imem_ready while a slot exists.\n30:       Output mux selects buffer, direct imem_data, or NOP based on buffer\n31:       occupancy and imem_ready.  Accept stall_core (load-use + dmem only)\n32:       and imem_ready directly instead of the old stall/flush pair.\n33:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n34:     description: |\n35:       Remove imem_stall from stall_if so that the pipeline only stalls for\n36:       load-use hazards and dmem stalls.  Reduce flush_if to redirect only;\n37:       imem backpressure is now handled locally inside if_stage.\n38:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n39:     description: |\n40:       Wire io_imemReady directly to if_stage and connect the new stall_core\n41:       signal from hazard_unit to if_stage.  Remove the old stall_if / flush_if\n42:       plumbing that coupled imem backpressure to the whole pipeline.\n\n(End of file - total 42 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260514-002-r5s1\ntitle: Add 1-entry instruction prefetch buffer to hide imem stalls\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The IF stage currently stalls the entire pipeline on every imem_ready=0 cycle,\n  injecting a NOP bubble into ID/EX. At the same time, during load-use or dmem\n  stalls the PC holds even though imem may be ready, wasting a fetch slot.\n  Decoupling fetch from issue with a 1-entry buffer lets us prefetch one\n  instruction ahead during downstream stalls and then issue it when imem\n  subsequently stalls, hiding single-cycle bus bubbles without lengthening\n  any critical path.\nhypothesis: |\n  Restructure if_stage to hold a 1-entry prefetch buffer (buf_pc, buf_instr,\n  buf_pred_taken, buf_valid).  The fetch PC advances whenever imem_ready is\n  high and there is a free buffer slot.  An instruction is issued to ID from\n  the buffer if available, otherwise directly from imem_data, and only a\n  true NOP is emitted when both sources are empty.  In hazard_unit, stop\n  treating imem_ready=0 as a global stall_if / flush_if event; instead let\n  if_stage backpressure itself locally.  This structural decoupling turns\n  otherwise-wasted fetch slots during load-use/dmem stalls into prefetches,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r5s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778732228795,"end":1778732228799}},"id":"prt_e24b3dea6002fjPw3kG9PPLT8z","sessionID":"ses_1db5569ebffe2V7Cl9b41fgi86","messageID":"msg_e24b3cdd8001n3Jxr5b19LICc8"}}
