{"type":"text","timestamp":1778732236452,"sessionID":"ses_1db5569ebffe2V7Cl9b41fgi86","part":{"id":"prt_e24b3f458003RjYbsL9DJhtZ5Q","messageID":"msg_e24b3e404001TcpkTFhnFYZxmY","sessionID":"ses_1db5569ebffe2V7Cl9b41fgi86","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r5s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Add a 1-entry instruction prefetch buffer in `if_stage` to decouple fetch from issue. The buffer fills during otherwise-wasted fetch slots (load-use or dmem stalls when `imem_ready=1`) and drains into ID when `imem_ready` drops, hiding single-cycle imem bubbles without touching any critical path. `hazard_unit` is simplified to stop treating `imem_ready=0` as a global pipeline stall. Expected impact: **+3% fitness** (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778732233816,"end":1778732236451}}}
