the cfg.\n39: @basedir@/cores/@core@/core.sv\n40: @basedir@/cores/@core@/wrapper.sv\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"[options]\nisa rv32im\nnret 1\nsolver bitwuzla\n\n[depth]\n# BMC depth per check. 2nd column (where present) is the k-induction prove\n# depth. Keep depths matched to the current pipeline so bugs within ~20\n# cycles of any symbolic instruction stream are exposed.\ninsn          20\nreg       10  20\npc_fwd    10  20\npc_bwd    10  20\ncausal    10  20\n# unique   — no two retirements share rvfi_order (catches double-retire)\n# cover    — sanity that the CPU retires (prevents vacuous-pass suites)\n# ill      — illegal instructions must trap; rvfi_trap from decoder.is_illegal\n# liveness — CPU makes forward progress under any symbolic stream\nunique     1 10 20\ncover      1    20","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"formal/checks_si.cfg","time":{"start":1778736443467,"end":1778736443476}},"id":"prt_e24f42eff001BGtQtUGULgAFac","sessionID":"ses_1db13f5b1ffeB0Ml9LQdwP7u82","messageID":"msg_e24f34c4b0010Z6fofmQjXYt0s"}}
