{"type":"text","timestamp":1778736785351,"sessionID":"ses_1db13f5b1ffeB0Ml9LQdwP7u82","part":{"id":"prt_e24f95b7c0010owZw1kGVs93C4","messageID":"msg_e24f94876001TlDJqXFmXCn3yR","sessionID":"ses_1db13f5b1ffeB0Ml9LQdwP7u82","type":"text","text":"I've written the structural hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r7s1.yaml`.\n\n**Proposal: Replace the combinational divider with a 33-cycle iterative unit.**\n\nThe combinational divider inferred from SystemVerilog `/` and `%` consumes ~52% of the core's cell count and creates severe routing congestion around the EX stage. Because division is essentially unused in CoreMark, moving it to a compact multi-cycle FSM should improve Fmax with negligible IPC loss. The previous attempt at this failed due to a deadlock-prone state machine; this hypothesis explicitly requires a correct IDLE→RUNNING→DONE FSM where `busy` is low in the DONE cycle, allowing clean handoff to the pipeline stall logic.","time":{"start":1778736782204,"end":1778736785348}}}
