{"type":"text","timestamp":1778742037091,"sessionID":"ses_1dac84d93ffeovARKJoi7VUZtl","part":{"id":"prt_e25497242001m01czlo0oIV2Ei","messageID":"msg_e2549436e002yExivznzLbuYJo","sessionID":"ses_1dac84d93ffeovARKJoi7VUZtl","type":"text","text":"Done. The hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-002-r9s1.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the proposed structural hypothesis:**\n\n- **Idea:** Add a 2-entry instruction skid buffer inside `if_stage` to decouple fetch from issue.\n- **Why:** The eval contract injects ~22% random stalls on `io_imemReady`. Currently every stalled cycle freezes the PC and flushes ID, creating a bubble. A 2-entry buffer lets the core prefetch when the downstream pipeline is stalled (load-use / dmem) and then continue issuing during subsequent imem stalls, hiding single-cycle (and many multi-cycle) bus bubbles.\n- **Expected impact:** ~10% fitness gain (medium confidence) from higher effective fetch throughput, with negligible Fmax impact (~130 flops, no new long combinational paths).\n- **Files changed:**\n  1. `rtl/if_stage.sv` — add the ring buffer, fetch/issue mux, and local backpressure.\n  2. `rtl/hazard_unit.sv` — remove `imem_ready` from `stall_if` / `flush_if` so imem backpressure is no longer a global pipeline stall.\n  3. `rtl/core.sv` — wire `io_imemReady` into `if_stage`; no top-level IO changes.","time":{"start":1778742030914,"end":1778742037087}}}
