{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778745610995,"sessionID":"ses_1da8c0d24ffeyR5lnSLdShWPv7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\ntitle: Add 8-entry loop predictor for backward branch exits\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\n  backward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\n  of every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\n  many small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\n  this exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\n  the trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\n  the last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\n  mispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add an 8-entry direct-mapped loop predictor table to the IF stage.\n  Each entry stores a tag, a trained iteration length, a speculative\n  down-counter, and a 1-bit confidence flag.\n  When a backward branch is fetched, if the entry is valid, tag matches,\n  and confidence is high, the predictor overrides the BHT:\n    - down-counter > 0  → predict taken and decrement the counter.\n    - down-counter == 0 → predict not-taken.\n  In EX, resolved backward branches update the table:\n    - During training (confidence low) the table counts taken outcomes;\n      the first not-taken exit stores the count as the trained length\n      and sets confidence high.\n    - On a correct exit (predicted not-taken) the counter is reloaded\n      from the trained length for the next loop invocation.\n    - On a length mismatch (mispredict) confidence is cleared so the\n      entry re-trains on the next invocation.\n  This attacks the last predictable bubble source without touching the\n  existing BHT or pipeline bundles.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add 8-entry loop-predictor array (tag, length, count, conf), combinational read/decrement, and integrate with predict_taken so a matching confident entry overrides the BHT for backward branches.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add loop-predictor update logic: on resolved backward branches allocate/train entries, reload counters on correct exits, and clear confidence on mispredicts. Drive update signals back to IF.\"\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add loop_predictor_entry_t struct and confidence constants to the package.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire the new loop-predictor update signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r11s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r11s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r11s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778745610984,"end":1778745610994}},"id":"prt_e257fdae6001Xtyn1GdQFFlpNb","sessionID":"ses_1da8c0d24ffeyR5lnSLdShWPv7","messageID":"msg_e257d6564001xlHwSNB3D2hkNE"}}
