{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778745627178,"sessionID":"ses_1da8c0d24ffeyR5lnSLdShWPv7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"import yaml, json, sys; data = yaml.safe_load(open('/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r11s2.yaml')); json.dump(data, sys.stdout, indent=2); print()\"","description":"Validate written YAML file"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 8-entry loop predictor for backward branch exits\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\\nbackward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\\nof every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped loop predictor table to the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a tag, a trained iteration length, a speculative\\ndown-counter, and a 1-bit confidence flag.\\nWhen a backward branch is fetched, if the entry is valid, tag matches,\\nand confidence is high, the predictor overrides the BHT:\\n  - down-counter > 0  \\u2192 predict taken and decrement the counter.\\n  - down-counter == 0 \\u2192 predict not-taken.\\nIn EX, resolved backward branches update the table:\\n  - During training (confidence low) the table counts taken outcomes;\\n    the first not-taken exit stores the count as the trained length\\n    and sets confidence high.\\n  - On a correct exit (predicted not-taken) the counter is reloaded\\n    from the trained length for the next loop invocation.\\n  - On a length mismatch (mispredict) confidence is cleared so the\\n    entry re-trains on the next invocation.\\nThis attacks the last predictable bubble source without touching the\\nexisting BHT or pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add 8-entry loop-predictor array (tag, length, count, conf), combinational read/decrement, and integrate with predict_taken so a matching confident entry overrides the BHT for backward branches.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop-predictor update logic: on resolved backward branches allocate/train entries, reload counters on correct exits, and clear confidence on mispredicts. Drive update signals back to IF.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop_predictor_entry_t struct and confidence constants to the package.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new loop-predictor update signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 8-entry loop predictor for backward branch exits\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\\nbackward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\\nof every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped loop predictor table to the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a tag, a trained iteration length, a speculative\\ndown-counter, and a 1-bit confidence flag.\\nWhen a backward branch is fetched, if the entry is valid, tag matches,\\nand confidence is high, the predictor overrides the BHT:\\n  - down-counter > 0  \\u2192 predict taken and decrement the counter.\\n  - down-counter == 0 \\u2192 predict not-taken.\\nIn EX, resolved backward branches update the table:\\n  - During training (confidence low) the table counts taken outcomes;\\n    the first not-taken exit stores the count as the trained length\\n    and sets confidence high.\\n  - On a correct exit (predicted not-taken) the counter is reloaded\\n    from the trained length for the next loop invocation.\\n  - On a length mismatch (mispredict) confidence is cleared so the\\n    entry re-trains on the next invocation.\\nThis attacks the last predictable bubble source without touching the\\nexisting BHT or pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add 8-entry loop-predictor array (tag, length, count, conf), combinational read/decrement, and integrate with predict_taken so a matching confident entry overrides the BHT for backward branches.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop-predictor update logic: on resolved backward branches allocate/train entries, reload counters on correct exits, and clear confidence on mispredicts. Drive update signals back to IF.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop_predictor_entry_t struct and confidence constants to the package.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new loop-predictor update signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Validate written YAML file","truncated":false},"title":"Validate written YAML file","time":{"start":1778745627175,"end":1778745627178}},"id":"prt_e2580497e00154tYYlMkUqo2x5","sessionID":"ses_1da8c0d24ffeyR5lnSLdShWPv7","messageID":"msg_e25801f22001MKrALnCg1JJ6yr"}}
