{"type":"text","timestamp":1778747983513,"sessionID":"ses_1da61a41affeTX9L0P7xbsplOu","part":{"id":"prt_e25a42428001BamBiPdj4SpzV9","messageID":"msg_e25a3e7ba001Pg3L6vwMJrzEaF","sessionID":"ses_1da61a41affeTX9L0P7xbsplOu","type":"text","text":"Done. The hypothesis file has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r12s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:**\n- **Category:** predictor\n- **Idea:** Add a 4-entry Return-Address Stack (RAS) to the IF stage to predict JALR return targets.\n- **Mechanism:** Push PC+4 on JAL/JALR calls (rd = x1/x5); pop and predict on JALR returns (rd = x0, rs1 = x1/x5). Thread the predicted target through a new `pred_target` field in the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. EX stage only redirects on JALR mispredicts instead of unconditionally.\n- **Expected gain:** +4% fitness (medium confidence), by eliminating the 2-cycle redirect bubble on every correct function return in CoreMark.\n- **Files changed:** `core_pkg.sv`, `if_stage.sv`, `id_stage.sv`, `ex_stage.sv`.","time":{"start":1778747974696,"end":1778747983509}}}
