{"type":"text","timestamp":1778749892544,"sessionID":"ses_1da496ea7ffezAxTBNo3MtwKnx","part":{"id":"prt_e25c14f0e001X9EeUA34WLCxjr","messageID":"msg_e25c12da7001sprD7xO1ZR1oJz","sessionID":"ses_1da496ea7ffezAxTBNo3MtwKnx","type":"text","text":"Done. Wrote hypothesis `hyp-20260514-003-r13s2.yaml` to the experiments directory.\n\n**Summary:** Hash-mix higher PC bits (`pc[11:7]`) into the existing 32-entry BHT index via a 5-bit XOR. This scatters branches that alias on the low 5 bits without enlarging the table (avoiding the Fmax penalty that killed the 128-entry BHT) and without adding any state (avoiding the complexity that broke gshare and loop predictors). Changes touch only `rtl/if_stage.sv` and `rtl/ex_stage.sv`.","time":{"start":1778749886222,"end":1778749892541}}}
