culative IF-stage update with EX-stage restore\\nfixes the staleness while keeping the table small and the read path fast.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The 32-entry bimodal BHT already yielded +7.3% fitness, but a follow-up\\ngshare variant regressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated non-speculatively\\nin EX. By the time a branch resolved, the next branch had already been\\nfetched with stale history, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark\\ncontains short basic blocks with back-to-back branches where history\\nstaleness is fatal. A speculative IF-stage update with EX-stage restore\\nfixes the staleness while keeping the table small and the read path fast.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 5-bit Global History Register (GHR) to the IF stage and XOR it into\\nthe existing 32-entry BHT index (gshare). The GHR is updated speculatively\\nwhenever a conditional branch is fetched: ghr <= {ghr[3:0], predict_taken}.\\nThe pre-update GHR value is snapshotted into a new 5-bit field in the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles. In EX, when a conditional branch mispredicts\\n(redirect is asserted), the GHR is restored to {snapshot[3:0], actual_taken}\\nvia a new feedback port to IF. On correct prediction no restore is needed.\\nThe BHT write index uses pc[6:2] ^ snapshot so the counter update hits the\\nsame entry that was read during fetch. This gives history-aware prediction\\nwithout enlarging the array and with negligible combinational delay (a\\n5-bit XOR on an existi...\n  Line 31: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r10s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r10s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r10s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r10s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 10}\n\n  Line 34: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r11s2\", \"title\": \"Add 8-entry loop predictor for backward branch exits\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\\nbackward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\\nof every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\\nbackward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\\nof every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped loop predictor table to the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a tag, a trained iteration length, a speculative\\ndown-counter, and a 1-bit confidence flag.\\nWhen a backward branch is fetched, if the entry is valid, tag matches,\\nand confidence is high, the predictor overrides the BHT:\\n  - down-counter > 0  \\u2192 predict taken and decrement the counter.\\n  - down-counter == 0 \\u2192 predict not-taken.\\nIn EX, resolved backward branches update the table:\\n  - During training (confidence low) the table counts taken outcomes;\\n    the first not-taken exit stores the count as the trained length\\n    and sets confidence high.\\n  - On a correct ex...\n  Line 37: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r12s2\", \"title\": \"Add 4-entry return-address stack for JALR prediction\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current predictor correctly handles conditional branches (32-entry BHT)\\nand JAL (always-taken), but JALR is never predicted. Every function return\\ncauses a 2-cycle redirect bubble in EX. CoreMark contains many small function\\ncalls; a return-address stack predicts return targets with near-perfect\\naccuracy for a tiny area cost (~130 flops), improving IPC without degrading\\nFmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current predictor correctly handles conditional branches (32-entry BHT)\\nand JAL (always-taken), but JALR is never predicted. Every function return\\ncauses a 2-cycle redirect bubble in EX. CoreMark contains many small function\\ncalls; a return-address stack predicts return targets with near-perfect\\naccuracy for a tiny area cost (~130 flops), improving IPC without degrading\\nFmax.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry return-address stack (RAS) to the IF stage. Push PC+4 on\\nany JAL or JALR call (rd = x1/x5). Pop the RAS and predict taken on any\\nJALR return (rd = x0, rs1 = x1/x5). Thread the predicted target through a\\nnew `pred_target` field in the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. In EX stage,\\ncompare the actual JALR target with `pred_target`; only redirect on\\nmispredict or when JALR was not predicted. This eliminates the redirect\\nbubble on correct function returns.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add `pred_target` field to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t` structs.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add 4-entry RAS with push/pop control; use RAS top as predicted target for JALR returns; drive `out.pred_target`.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Thread `in.pred_target` into the ID/EX register.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Replace unconditional JALR redirect with mispredict detection using `in....\n  Line 40: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r13s2\", \"title\": \"Hash-mix higher PC bits into 32-entry BHT index to reduce aliasing\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter BHT is the proven sweet spot for\\nthis core, delivering a +7.3% fitness gain. A follow-up attempt to grow\\nthe table to 128 entries regressed -3% because the wider read mux hurt\\nFmax, while gshare global-history variants regressed due to history\\nstaleness. The remaining occasional forward-branch mispredictions may\\nstem from destructive aliasing among branches that share the low five\\nPC bits. A zero-cost hash that XORs higher PC bits into the index\\nscatters colliding branches without enlarging the array or adding any\\nnew state.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter BHT is the proven sweet spot for\\nthis core, delivering a +7.3% fitness gain. A follow-up attempt to grow\\nthe table to 128 entries regressed -3% because the wider read mux hurt\\nFmax, while gshare global-history variants regressed due to history\\nstaleness. The remaining occasional forward-branch mispredictions may\\nstem from destructive aliasing among branches that share the low five\\nPC bits. A zero-cost hash that XORs higher PC bits into the index\\nscatters colliding branches without enlarging the array or adding any\\nnew state.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Keep the proven 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter table unchanged, but\\nchange both the read index and the write-back index from pc[6:2] to\\npc[6:2] ^ pc[11:7]. In the IF stage this mixes bits 7-11 of the PC\\ninto the existing 5-bit index, reducing the chance that two branches\\nwhose lower five bits collide map to the same counter. In the EX stage\\nthe update index uses in.pc[6:2] ^ in.pc[11:7] so the counter write\\nhits exactly the entry that was read during fetch. The combinational\\ncost is a single 5-bit XOR, which Yosys will absorb into the existing\\nLUT fabric with negligible Fmax impact. No new flops, pipeline bundles,\\nor cont...","metadata":{"matches":13,"truncated":false},"title":"\"category\": \"predictor\"","time":{"start":1778750720065,"end":1778750720080}},"id":"prt_e25ce04bb001pff1AXnVeFAZ59","sessionID":"ses_1da325336fferLJv5DX6QjzZyq","messageID":"msg_e25cdad010010nNu0IGxuSxRNc"}}
