{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778751848424,"sessionID":"ses_1da325336fferLJv5DX6QjzZyq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r14s2\ntitle: \"Add single global loop-exit predictor to eliminate BHT loop-exit mispredictions\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The 32-entry 2-bit BHT saturates to strongly-taken for backward branches,\n  so it mispredicts the final iteration of every inner loop. CoreMark is\n  loop-heavy (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC) and these exit mispredictions\n  are the last systematic control bubble. A prior 8-entry tagged loop\n  predictor regressed because its tag-CAM and per-entry state machines\n  hurt Fmax. A single global loop counter needs only ~45 flops and one\n  32-bit PC comparator, giving loop-exit prediction with negligible\n  combinational overhead.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a single global loop-exit predictor to the IF stage. It keeps one\n  loop_pc (32-bit), one loop_len (8-bit), one loop_cnt (8-bit), and a\n  valid bit. When the fetched PC matches loop_pc and the branch is backward,\n  the predictor overrides the BHT: loop_cnt>0 predicts taken (and decrements),\n  loop_cnt==0 predicts not-taken. In EX, training is automatic: on every\n  backward branch that matches loop_pc, increment a training counter while\n  taken; on the first not-taken exit capture the count as loop_len and\n  reload loop_cnt. A new backward-branch mispredict in EX clears valid so\n  the predictor retrains safely. For all other branches the existing BHT\n  and JAL logic remain unchanged. This removes the 2-cycle bubble on every\n  correctly-predicted loop exit for minimal area and near-zero Fmax risk.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add loop_pc, loop_len, loop_cnt, loop_valid registers. Override BHT prediction with loop-exit logic when fetching the active backward branch. Decrement loop_cnt on use.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add loop training state machine: count taken iterations of the active backward branch, capture length on not-taken exit, reload counter, and clear loop_valid on backward-branch mispredict.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire loop training and clear signals from ex_stage back to if_stage. No top-level IO changes.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r14s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778751848413,"end":1778751848422}},"id":"prt_e25df0eee001yIc25UpvGUI225","sessionID":"ses_1da325336fferLJv5DX6QjzZyq","messageID":"msg_e25dedb78001mIzBFrfA5MPGf0"}}
