tually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT already captures forward branch directions and\\nbackward-taken bias, but it cannot avoid mispredicting the final iteration\\nof every loop (predicted taken, actually not-taken). CoreMark contains\\nmany small inner loops (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC updates) where\\nthis exit misprediction wastes cycles. A dedicated loop predictor learns\\nthe trip count of individual backward branches and predicts not-taken on\\nthe last iteration, removing the only remaining systematic direction\\nmispredictions with only ~100 flops and no wider BHT mux.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add an 8-entry direct-mapped loop predictor table to the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a tag, a trained iteration length, a speculative\\ndown-counter, and a 1-bit confidence flag.\\nWhen a backward branch is fetched, if the entry is valid, tag matches,\\nand confidence is high, the predictor overrides the BHT:\\n  - down-counter > 0  \\u2192 predict taken and decrement the counter.\\n  - down-counter == 0 \\u2192 predict not-taken.\\nIn EX, resolved backward branches update the table:\\n  - During training (confidence low) the table counts taken outcomes;\\n    the first not-taken exit stores the count as the trained length\\n    and sets confidence high.\\n  - On a correct exit (predicted not-taken) the counter is reloaded\\n    from the trained length for the next loop invocation.\\n  - On a length mismatch (mispredict) confidence is cleared so the\\n    entry re-trains on the next invocation.\\nThis attacks the last predictable bubble source without touching the\\nexisting BHT or pipeline bundles.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add 8-entry loop-predictor array (tag, length, count, conf), combinational read/decrement, and integrate with predict_taken so a matching confident entry overrides the BHT for backward branches.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add loop-predictor update logic: on resolved backward branches allocate/train entries, reload counters on correct exits, and clear confidence on mispredicts. Drive update signals back to IF.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add loop_predictor_entry_t struct and confidence constants to the package.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new loop-predictor update signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add 8-entry loop-predictor array (tag, length, count, conf), combinational read/decrement, and integrate with predict_taken so a matching confident entry overrides the BHT for backward branches.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop-predictor update logic: on resolved backward branches allocate/train entries, reload counters on correct exits, and clear confidence on mispredicts. Drive update signals back to IF.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop_predictor_entry_t struct and confidence constants to the package.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new loop-predictor update signals between ex_stage and if_stage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 302.03,\n  \"delta_pct\": -13.15,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 6.79,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 126.68,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4194286,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10454,\n  \"ff\": 1951,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    114.19,\n    126.68,\n    139.82\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T08:24:35.661190Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 11,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe rewrote /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/LESSONS.md instead of appending; reverted to prior content\"\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r12s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 4-entry return-address stack for JALR prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current predictor correctly handles conditional branches (32-entry BHT)\\nand JAL (always-taken), but JALR is never predicted. Every function return\\ncauses a 2-cycle redirect bubble in EX. CoreMark contains many small function\\ncalls; a return-address stack predicts return targets with near-perfect\\naccuracy for a tiny area cost (~130 flops), improving IPC without degrading\\nFmax.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current predictor correctly handles conditional branches (32-entry BHT)\\nand JAL (always-taken), but JALR is never predicted. Every function return\\ncauses a 2-cycle redirect bubble in EX. CoreMark contains many small function\\ncalls; a return-address stack predicts return targets with near-perfect\\naccuracy for a tiny area cost (~130 flops), improving IPC without degrading\\nFmax.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 4-entry return-address stack (RAS) to the IF stage. Push PC+4 on\\nany JAL or JALR call (rd = x1/x5). Pop the RAS and predict taken on any\\nJALR return (rd = x0, rs1 = x1/x5). Thread the predicted target through a\\nnew `pred_target` field in the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. In EX stage,\\ncompare the actual JALR target with `pred_target`; only redirect on\\nmispredict or when JALR was not predicted. This eliminates the redirect\\nbubble on correct function returns.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add `pred_target` field to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t` structs.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add 4-entry RAS with push/pop control; use RAS top as predicted target for JALR returns; drive `out.pred_target`.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread `in.pred_target` into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace unconditional JALR redirect with mispredict detection using `in.pred_target`; only redirect when JALR was not predicted or target mismatches.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add `pred_target` field to `if_id_t` and `id_ex_t` structs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add 4-entry RAS with push/pop control; use RAS top as predicted target for JALR returns; drive `out.pred_target`.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread `in.pred_target` into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace unconditional JALR redirect with mispredict detection using `in.pred_target`; only redirect when JALR was not predicted or target mismatches.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 347.76,\n  \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 22.96,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10254,\n  \"ff\": 1940,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    146.18,\n    132.82,\n    146.26\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T08:56:28.477087Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 12\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r13s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Hash-mix higher PC bits into 32-entry BHT index to reduce aliasing\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter BHT is the proven sweet spot for\\nthis core, delivering a +7.3% fitness gain. A follow-up attempt to grow\\nthe table to 128 entries regressed -3% because the wider read mux hurt\\nFmax, while gshare global-history variants regressed due to history\\nstaleness. The remaining occasional forward-branch mispredictions may\\nstem from destructive aliasing among branches that share the low five\\nPC bits. A zero-cost hash that XORs higher PC bits into the index\\nscatters colliding branches without enlarging the array or adding any\\nnew state.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter BHT is the proven sweet spot for\\nthis core, delivering a +7.3% fitness gain. A follow-up attempt to grow\\nthe table to 128 entries regressed -3% because the wider read mux hurt\\nFmax, while gshare global-history variants regressed due to history\\nstaleness. The remaining occasional forward-branch mispredictions may\\nstem from destructive aliasing among branches that share the low five\\nPC bits. A zero-cost hash that XORs higher PC bits into the index\\nscatters colliding branches without enlarging the array or adding any\\nnew state.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Keep the proven 32-entry 2-bit saturating-counter table unchanged, but\\nchange both the read index and the write-back index from pc[6:2] to\\npc[6:2] ^ pc[11:7]. In the IF stage this mixes bits 7-11 of the PC\\ninto the existing 5-bit index, reducing the chance that two branches\\nwhose lower five bits collide map to the same counter. In the EX stage\\nthe update index uses in.pc[6:2] ^ in.pc[11:7] so the counter write\\nhits exactly the entry that was read during fetch. The combinational\\ncost is a single 5-bit XOR, which Yosys will absorb into the existing\\nLUT fabric with negligible Fmax impact. No new flops, pipeline bundles,\\nor control signals are introduced.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 2,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Change BHT read index from pc[6:2] to pc[6:2] ^ pc[11:7].\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Change BHT update index from in.pc[6:2] to in.pc[6:2] ^ in.pc[11:7].\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 2,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Change BHT read index from pc[6:2] to pc[6:2] ^ pc[11:7].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Change BHT update index from in.pc[6:2] to in.pc[6:2] ^ in.pc[11:7].\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 235.82,\n  \"delta_pct\": -32.19,\n  \"vs_baseline\": -16.62,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 99.0,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4198050,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10363,\n  \"ff\": 1934,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    99.0,\n    105.12,\n    96.15\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T09:19:06.627254Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 13,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r14s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add single global loop-exit predictor to eliminate BHT loop-exit mispredictions\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT saturates to strongly-taken for backward branches,\\nso it mispredicts the final iteration of every inner loop. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC) and these exit mispredictions\\nare the last systematic control bubble. A prior 8-entry tagged loop\\npredictor regressed because its tag-CAM and per-entry state machines\\nhurt Fmax. A single global loop counter needs only ~45 flops and one\\n32-bit PC comparator, giving loop-exit prediction with negligible\\ncombinational overhead.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry 2-bit BHT saturates to strongly-taken for backward branches,\\nso it mispredicts the final iteration of every inner loop. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy (list traversal, matrix rows, CRC) and these exit mispredictions\\nare the last systematic control bubble. A prior 8-entry tagged loop\\npredictor regressed because its tag-CAM and per-entry state machines\\nhurt Fmax. A single global loop counter needs only ~45 flops and one\\n32-bit PC comparator, giving loop-exit prediction with negligible\\ncombinational overhead.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a single global loop-exit predictor to the IF stage. It keeps one\\nloop_pc (32-bit), one loop_len (8-bit), one loop_cnt (8-bit), and a\\nvalid bit. When the fetched PC matches loop_pc and the branch is backward,\\nthe predictor overrides the BHT: loop_cnt>0 predicts taken (and decrements),\\nloop_cnt==0 predicts not-taken. In EX, training is automatic: on every\\nbackward branch that matches loop_pc, increment a training counter while\\ntaken; on the first not-taken exit capture the count as loop_len and\\nreload loop_cnt. A new backward-branch mispredict in EX clears valid so\\nthe predictor retrains safely. For all other branches the existing BHT\\nand JAL logic remain unchanged. This removes the 2-cycle bubble on every\\ncorrectly-predicted loop exit for minimal area and near-zero Fmax risk.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add loop_pc, loop_len, loop_cnt, loop_valid registers. Override BHT prediction with loop-exit logic when fetching the active backward branch. Decrement loop_cnt on use.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add loop training state machine: count taken iterations of the active backward branch, capture length on not-taken exit, reload counter, and clear loop_valid on backward-branch mispredict.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire loop training and clear signals from ex_stage back to if_stage. No top-level IO changes.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop_pc, loop_len, loop_cnt, loop_valid registers. Override BHT prediction with loop-exit logic when fetching the active backward branch. Decrement loop_cnt on use.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add loop training state machine: count taken iterations of the active backward branch, capture length on not-taken exit, reload counter, and clear loop_valid on backward-branch mispredict.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire loop training and clear signals from ex_stage back to if_stage. No top-level IO changes.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 282.24,\n  \"delta_pct\": -18.84,\n  \"vs_baseline\": -0.21,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 118.64,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4203461