field to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 5-bit ghr register initialised to 0. Compute BHT read index as pc[6:2] ^ ghr. Drive the current ghr value into out.ghr_snapshot. On non-stalled, non-flushed cycles where the fetched instruction is a conditional branch, speculatively update ghr <= {ghr[3:0], predict_taken}. Add a new input port ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en; when restore_en is asserted on redirect from EX, reload ghr with ghr_restore.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Capture in.ghr_snapshot into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Compute BHT update index as in.pc[6:2] ^ in.ghr_snapshot so the counter update writes the exact entry that was read during fetch. Add output ports ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en. Drive ghr_restore = {in.ghr_snapshot[3:0], branch_taken} and assert ghr_restore_en whenever redirect is asserted for a conditional branch (in.ctrl.is_branch). JAL/JALR redirects must not assert restore_en.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new ghr_restore/ghr_restore_en signals from ex_stage back to if_stage.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r8s2\",\n  \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r8s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r8s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r8s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r8s2'])\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 8\n}\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r9s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Fix gshare by speculatively updating GHR in IF with mispredict restore\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry bimodal BHT already yielded +7.3% fitness, but a follow-up\\ngshare variant regressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated non-speculatively\\nin EX. By the time a branch resolved, the next branch had already been\\nfetched with stale history, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark\\ncontains short basic blocks with back-to-back branches where history\\nstaleness is fatal. A speculative IF-stage update with EX-stage restore\\nfixes the staleness while keeping the table small and the read path fast.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The 32-entry bimodal BHT already yielded +7.3% fitness, but a follow-up\\ngshare variant regressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated non-speculatively\\nin EX. By the time a branch resolved, the next branch had already been\\nfetched with stale history, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark\\ncontains short basic blocks with back-to-back branches where history\\nstaleness is fatal. A speculative IF-stage update with EX-stage restore\\nfixes the staleness while keeping the table small and the read path fast.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 5-bit Global History Register (GHR) to the IF stage and XOR it into\\nthe existing 32-entry BHT index (gshare). The GHR is updated speculatively\\nwhenever a conditional branch is fetched: ghr <= {ghr[3:0], predict_taken}.\\nThe pre-update GHR value is snapshotted into a new 5-bit field in the\\nIF/ID and ID/EX bundles. In EX, when a conditional branch mispredicts\\n(redirect is asserted), the GHR is restored to {snapshot[3:0], actual_taken}\\nvia a new feedback port to IF. On correct prediction no restore is needed.\\nThe BHT write index uses pc[6:2] ^ snapshot so the counter update hits the\\nsame entry that was read during fetch. This gives history-aware prediction\\nwithout enlarging the array and with negligible combinational delay (a\\n5-bit XOR on an existing mux path).\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 4,\n      