{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778753823278,"sessionID":"ses_1da08a948ffexAF2vXJ8iXXlVW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r15s2\ntitle: Exclude backward branches from BHT to eliminate aliasing pollution on forward branches\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current 32-entry 2-bit BHT is indexed by PC[6:2] and updated for every\n  resolved conditional branch. Backward branches (loops) are almost always\n  taken and saturate their entries to 2'b11 almost immediately. When a\n  forward branch happens to alias with a hot backward branch, the backward\n  branch’s constant \"taken\" updates keep overwriting the forward branch’s\n  state, preventing the forward branch from ever training to its true bias.\n  This destructive aliasing is the largest remaining accuracy loss in the\n  32-entry table, yet it can be fixed with zero extra hardware: backward\n  branches can be predicted statically taken (they already are) and simply\n  omitted from the BHT update path, freeing their index slots exclusively\n  for forward branches.\n\n  Prior attempts to reduce aliasing (128-entry BHT, gshare, hash-mixing)\n  all failed because they enlarged combinational paths or added flop state.\n  This approach removes updates, adds no state, and shortens no paths — it\n  only improves the *quality* of the information stored in the existing 32\n  entries.\n\nhypothesis: |\n  Modify the IF-stage direction prediction so that backward branches are\n  predicted taken unconditionally, bypassing the BHT read result.  In the\n  EX stage, gate the BHT update enable with the condition that the branch\n  immediate is positive (i.e. forward), so backward branches never write\n  the table.  Specifically:\n\n  1. In rtl/if_stage.sv, compute `is_backward = is_branch_instr && b_imm[31]`\n     and change `predict_taken` to `(is_branch_instr && (is_backward || bht_pred)) || is_jal_instr`.\n  2. In rtl/ex_stage.sv, change `bht_update_en` from\n     `!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch` to\n     `!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch && !in.imm[31]`.\n\n  No pipeline bundles, top-level IO, or BHT size changes are required.\n  Backward branches retain their existing loop-exit mispredict behaviour,\n  while forward branches that previously aliased with backward branches\n  now train correctly.\n\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\n\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add a combinational `is_backward` flag (`is_branch_instr && b_imm[31]`)\n      and alter `predict_taken` so backward branches are always predicted\n      taken without consulting the BHT.  Forward branches continue to use\n      `bht_pred`.  The BHT array itself is untouched.\n\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Qualify `bht_update_en` with `!in.imm[31]` so that only forward\n      conditional branches write the BHT.  Backward branches and all\n      non-branch instructions leave the table unchanged.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r15s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r15s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r15s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778753823263,"end":1778753823277}},"id":"prt_e25fd2448001GmvclX1IcY3AT8","sessionID":"ses_1da08a948ffexAF2vXJ8iXXlVW","messageID":"msg_e25f7adc4001hikvBGo54AJRjy"}}
