{"type":"text","timestamp":1778753857187,"sessionID":"ses_1da08a948ffexAF2vXJ8iXXlVW","part":{"id":"prt_e25fdd321001IB2xP2jAHSQZ0F","messageID":"msg_e25fdaaf30010PwqhL71ccKa9n","sessionID":"ses_1da08a948ffexAF2vXJ8iXXlVW","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis file written and schema-validated:\n\n**`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r15s2.yaml`**\n\n**Idea:** Exclude backward branches from the 32-entry BHT update path. Backward branches are already predicted correctly by the static taken-bias, so they don't need the table. By stopping them from writing the BHT, forward branches that alias on `PC[6:2]` are no longer polluted by constantly being reset to strongly-taken. This improves forward-branch accuracy with zero extra flops, no wider muxes, and no critical-path extension.\n\n**Expected impact:** +2% fitness (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778753852193,"end":1778753857185}}}
