h rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\\nfetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\\npop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\\npred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\\nID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\\nredirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\\ndiffers from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\\nnon-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\\nreturns.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 297.42,\n  \"delta_pct\": -8.23,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 5.16,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 126.28,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10086,\n  \"ff\": 1950,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    123.23,\n    135.1,\n    126.28\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:34:32.311729Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\",\n  \"title\": \"Eliminate false load-use stalls via opcode-aware hazard detection\",\n  \"category\": \"micro_opt\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current hazard_unit conservatively checks both rs1 (instr[19:15]) and rs2\\n(instr[24:20]) of the instruction in ID against the LOAD's rd in EX,\\nregardless of whether the instruction actually reads those fields as registers.\\nFor I-type (OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR), U-type, and J-type instructions, the rs2\\nfield is an immediate/shamt, not a register address. A LOAD followed by an\\nADDI where imm[4:0] happens to match the LOAD's rd currently triggers a\\nspurious one-cycle stall. CoreMark uses small immediate values extensively,\\nso false stalls on common x1-x5 register numbers are likely frequent.\\nEliminating these false stalls improves IPC with negligible LUT/Fmax cost.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add opcode decoding to hazard_unit so load-use detection only fires when\\nthe instruction in ID actually reads rs1/rs2 as registers. R-type, I-type\\n(OP-IMM/LOAD/JALR), S-type, and B-type use rs1; R-type, S-type, and B-type\\nuse rs2. U-type and J-type use neither. This removes false stalls without\\naltering pipeline structure or lengthening critical paths.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add opcode input and uses_rs1/uses_rs2 qualification to the load_use_hazard check.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire if_id_w.instr[6:0] to the hazard_unit's new opcode input.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add opcode input and uses_rs1/uses_rs2 qualification to the load_use_hazard check.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire if_id_w.instr[6:0] to the hazard_unit's new opcode input.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"cosim_failed: selftest.elf\",\n  \"slot\": 0,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n---\n{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 32-entry tagged BTB with 2-bit saturating counters for branch target caching and forward-branch learning\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor correctly predicts backward branches and JAL,\\nbut forward branches that are frequently taken are always mispredicted.\\nAdditionally, the combinational branch-target computation in the IF stage\\n(opcode decode \\u2192 immediate extraction \\u2192 sign-extension \\u2192 PC adder) may\\ncontribute to the critical path. A small Branch Target Buffer can learn\\ntaken forward branches, cache targets to shorten the IF-stage path, and\\ncoexist safely with the existing static BTFN predictor.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch Target Buffer in the IF stage.\\nEach entry stores a valid bit, a 5-bit tag (PC[11:7]), a 30-bit\\nword-aligned target, and a 2-bit saturating counter.  In IF, a BTB\\nhit on a branch or JAL supplies the target directly from a register\\nread, bypassing the combinational immediate+adder path.  Direction\\nprediction remains static-taken for backward branches and JAL, but\\nthe BTB can additionally predict taken for forward branches once\\ntheir counter reaches 2.  In EX, every resolved branch/JAL writes\\nits outcome and target back into the BTB.  JALR is excluded from\\nBTB usage to avoid aliasing noise.  This should improve IPC on\\ntaken forward branches and may raise Fmax by reducing IF-stage\\ncombinational delay.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 5,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a packed `btb_entry_t` struct (valid, tag[4:0], target[29:0],\\ncounter[1:0]) for the 32-entry Branch Target Buffer.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add the 32-entry BTB array and combinational read logic.  Use the\\nBTB target on hit for branches/JAL, falling back to the existing\\ncombinational immediate+adder path on miss.  Add `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx`, and `btb_update_entry` input ports so EX can\\nwrite resolved outcomes back.  Keep the static backward-taken/JAL\\nprediction as a base; allow BTB to override only to predict taken\\nfor forward branches when the counter is saturated.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add combinational BTB update logic that drives `btb_update_en`,\\n`btb_update_idx` (from `in.pc[6:2]`), and `btb_update_entry`\\n(valid=1, tag=PC[11:7], target=resolved target, counter updated\\nby the 2-bit saturating counter rule) on every resolved branch\\nor jump.  Gate the update on `!stall && in.valid`.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate new wires `btb_update_en`, `btb_update_idx[4:0]`, and\\n`btb_update_entry` and route them from `ex_stage` outputs to\\n`if_stage` inputs so the BTB can be updated from EX.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"broken\",\n  \"formal_passed\": false,\n  \"cosim_passed\": false,\n  \"error\": \"cosim_failed: coremark.elf\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 3,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n---\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR return prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches