{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778728932739,"sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    d = json.loads(line)\n    if d['id'] == 'hyp-20260513-003-r1s2':\n        print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n        break\n\"","description":"Check BTFN predictor outcome"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Static BTFN branch predictor + JAL prediction in ID stage\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage pipeline resolves all control-flow instructions in EX and pays a\\nfixed 2-cycle bubble (flush IF/ID) for every taken branch and every jump. CoreMark is\\nloop-heavy; backward branches are taken the vast majority of the time. A static\\nBackward-Taken / Forward-Not-Taken (BTFN) predictor combined with unconditional JAL\\nprediction, both computed in the ID stage, eliminates the 2-cycle penalty for the\\nmost common control-flow cases at virtually zero area cost.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"confidence\": \"high\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add `logic predict_taken` field to the `id_ex_t` struct.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Compute `predict_taken` in decode (JAL || backward branch).  Add combinational\\noutputs `predict_redirect` and `predict_target` driven from the ID/EX register;\\nassert `predict_redirect` when `reg_q` is a predicted-taken control-flow instruction\\nand capture `predict_taken` into the ID/EX register.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Accept `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` inputs.  Give them priority over `stall`\\nbut below the EX-stage `redirect`.  Flush the combinational IF/ID output (NOP) on\\n`predict_redirect` so the fall-through instruction is discarded.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Use the new `in.predict_taken` bit to distinguish correct predictions from\\nmispredictions.  Assert `redirect` only when a branch mispredicts; for correctly\\npredicted jumps do not assert `redirect`.  Keep the existing misalignment-trap\\nlogic untouched.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Wire the new `predict_redirect` / `predict_target` signals from `id_stage` to\\n`if_stage`, and connect the ID-stage `predict_taken` path into the `id_ex_t` bundle.\\nNo top-level IO changes; RVFI and memory interfaces remain identical.\\n\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitnes