{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778728987709,"sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    d = json.loads(line)\n    if d['id'] == 'hyp-20260513-002-r1s1':\n        print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n        break\n\"","description":"Check static predictor fitness details"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Insert decode-and-predict logic in the IF stage. When the fetched instruction is\\na BRANCH with a negative immediate (backward loop) or an unconditional JAL, the\\nPC is updated to the computed target instead of PC+4. A 1-bit pred_taken flag is\\nthreaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. The EX stage suppresses redirect\\nwhen the prediction was correct; it only asserts redirect (triggering IF/ID flush)\\non mispredict. JALR remains unpredicted. This saves one cycle per correctly\\npredicted taken branch or JAL.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 324.08,\n  \"delta_pct\": 14.59,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 14.59,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10189,\n  \"ff\": 1874,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    133.46,\n    138.05,\n    148.35\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:11:08.300480Z\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 1,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r1s1 (improvement, +14.59%): Even a trivial static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken) eliminates the taken-branch bubble and yields double-digit IPC gains on loop-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark, with negligible LUT cost.\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\",\n  \"title\": \"Add static branch predictor (backward-taken, JAL-always-taken)\",\n  \"category\": \"structural\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The current 5-stage core incurs a 1-cycle bubble on every taken branch and JAL\\nbecause IF always speculatively fetches PC+4. CoreMark is loop-heavy, so backward\\nbranches and function calls are frequent. A static predictor that fetches the\\ntarget for backward branches and JAL eliminates the bubble on the common case,\\nimproving IPC with negligible LUT cost (~50 LUTs) and no impact on the critical\\npath.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Insert decode-and-predict logic in the IF stage. When the fetched instruction is\\na BRANCH with a negative immediate (backward loop) or an unconditional JAL, the\\nPC is updated to the computed target instead of PC+4. A 1-bit pred_taken flag is\\nthreaded through the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles. The EX stage suppresses redirect\\nwhen the prediction was correct; it only asserts redirect (triggering IF/ID flush)\\non mispredict. JALR remains unpredicted. This saves one cycle per correctly\\npredicted taken branch or JAL.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 8,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add pred_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Decode BRANCH/JAL opcodes from imem_data, compute B/J immediates, set predict_taken for backward branches and JAL, and select next_pc from the predicted target when predict_taken is asserted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread pred_taken from the IF/ID combinational bundle into the ID/EX pipeline register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Replace the unconditional redirect logic with mispredict detection. redirect is asserted only when a conditional branch outcome differs from pred_taken, or for unpredicte JALR. Correctly predicted branches and JAL no longer flush the pipeline.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"improvement\",\n  \"fitness\": 324.08,\n  \"delta_pct\": 14.59,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 14.59,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 138.05,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4259699,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10189,\n  \"ff\": 1874,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    133.46,\n    138.05,\n    148.35\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:11:08.300480Z\",\n  \"slot\": 1,\n  \"round_id\": 1,\n  \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r1s1 (improvement, +14.59%): Even a trivial static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken) eliminates the taken-branch bubble and yields double-digit IPC gains on loop-heavy benchmarks like CoreMark, with negligible LUT cost.\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Check static predictor fitness details","truncated":false},"title":"Check static predictor fitness details","time":{"start":1778728987706,"end":1778728987708}},"id":"prt_e24826080001XqxiN1ph6FZq1x","sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","messageID":"msg_e24819b9200137OfxfgXrAXHM7"}}
