{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778729685334,"sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r4s2\ntitle: \"Add 32-entry 2-bit BHT for forward branch direction prediction\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The existing IF-stage static predictor (backward-taken + JAL-always-taken)\n  already eliminated the largest source of control bubbles, yielding a +14.6%\n  fitness gain. The remaining dynamic mispredictions come mainly from forward\n  conditional branches that are frequently taken (e.g. early exits, loop-internal\n  conditionals) and from JALR returns. A prior 4-entry RAS improved IPC by only\n  0.3% because returns are rare, while a 32-entry tagged BTB broke in cosim.\n  A saturating-counter BHT attacks the much larger forward-branch bubble source\n  with minimal area (64 flops) and no changes to pipeline bundles.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 32-entry direct-mapped Branch History Table with 2-bit saturating\n  counters to the IF stage. The table is indexed by PC[6:2] and initialized to\n  strongly-taken (2'b11) so backward loops are correct immediately without any\n  training cost. For every conditional branch, the BHT entry MSB drives\n  predict_taken; unconditional JAL continues to be always predicted taken. In\n  EX stage, each resolved branch writes its actual outcome back to the entry\n  indexed by the branch PC using a standard saturating update rule. This adds\n  only 64 flops and a few LUTs of combinational logic, does not widen any\n  pipeline register, and the BHT read is off the critical instruction-fetch path\n  because the PC is known at the start of the cycle while the opcode decode\n  (which selects the BHT result) happens later in parallel.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add a 32-entry x 2-bit BHT array inside the IF stage.  Combinational\n      read uses pc[6:2] to select the counter; the MSB becomes the direction\n      prediction for conditional branches.  Add three new input ports\n      (bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], bht_update_taken) and a saturating\n      update rule that increments on taken and decrements on not-taken.  Modify\n      predict_taken so that conditional branches use the BHT MSB while JAL\n      remains unconditionally taken.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add output ports bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and\n      bht_update_taken.  Drive bht_update_en high on every cycle a conditional\n      branch is resolved (!stall && in.valid && in.ctrl.is_branch).\n      bht_update_idx is in.pc[6:2] and bht_update_taken is the combinational\n      branch_taken signal.  No other EX-stage logic is changed.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: >\n      Instantiate new wires bht_update_en, bht_update_idx[4:0], and\n      bht_update_taken and route them from ex_stage outputs to if_stage inputs.\n      No top-level IO or RVFI changes.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778729685330,"end":1778729685334}},"id":"prt_e248cbe83001epc5Nm4f6WzKVQ","sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","messageID":"msg_e24826da7001mEqTfG42MAi25K"}}
