{"type":"text","timestamp":1778729694212,"sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","part":{"id":"prt_e248d2500001JayYcdbYKyldGT","messageID":"msg_e248d13cf001qU4YKBVmo7P9cl","sessionID":"ses_1db804752ffeL2PhxqDfU2WqGA","type":"text","text":"Done — the hypothesis YAML has been written to:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r4s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** The hypothesis proposes adding a **32-entry, 2-bit saturating-counter BHT** to the IF stage to learn directions for forward conditional branches. It builds on the existing static predictor (which already handles backward branches and JAL perfectly) while keeping area tiny (~64 flops, no pipeline-bundle changes) and avoiding the complexity that caused prior BTB/RAS attempts to fail or regress.","time":{"start":1778729690368,"end":1778729694211}}}
