{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778731693076,"sessionID":"ses_1db556982ffeOpDgGDUzASRGrB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"bash:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"import json; f=open('cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl'); lines=f.readlines(); [print(json.dumps(json.loads(l), indent=2)) for l in lines if 'hyp-20260513-003-r2s2' in l]\"","description":"Print log entry for RAS predictor"},"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR return prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\\nunconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\\nflush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\\nnested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\\ninstruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\\naddress on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\\nreturn target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\\nunconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\\nflush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\\nnested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\\ninstruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\\naddress on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\\nreturn target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\\ninstruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\\nfetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\\npop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\\npred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\\nID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\\nredirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\\ndiffers from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\\nnon-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\\nreturns.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 297.42,\n  \"delta_pct\": -8.23,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 5.16,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 126.28,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10086,\n  \"ff\": 1950,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    123.23,\n    135.1,\n    126.28\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:34:32.311729Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\n  \"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\",\n  \"title\": \"Add 4-entry Return Address Stack for JALR return prediction\",\n  \"category\": \"predictor\",\n  \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\\nunconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\\nflush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\\nnested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\\ninstruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\\naddress on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\\nreturn target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\\n\",\n  \"hypothesis\": {\n    \"motivation\": \"The existing static predictor eliminates bubbles for backward branches and\\nunconditional JAL, but every JALR (function return) still incurs a 1-cycle\\nflush because the target is unknown until EX. CoreMark contains frequent\\nnested function calls, so returns are a noticeable fraction of the dynamic\\ninstruction stream. A tiny Return Address Stack (RAS) pushes the link\\naddress on JAL-to-x1/x5 and pops it on JALR-from-x1/x5, predicting the\\nreturn target in IF with high accuracy at negligible area cost.\\n\",\n    \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\\ninstruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\\nfetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\\npop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\\npred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\\nID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\\nredirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\\ndiffers from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\\nnon-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\\nreturns.\\n\",\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    \"changes\": [\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n        \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"expected_impact\": {\n    \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"confidence\": \"medium\"\n  },\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Add a 32-bit pred_target field to if_id_t and id_ex_t so the predicted address can flow to EX for mispredict checking.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Instantiate a 4-entry RAS. Detect call (JAL rd=x1/x5) and return (JALR rs1=x1/x5) patterns from imem_data, push/pop accordingly, and drive predict_taken/predict_target for returns.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"Thread the new pred_target bit from the IF/ID bundle into the ID/EX register.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\",\n      \"description\": \"For JALR, assert redirect only on mispredict (unpredicted or predicted target != actual jump_target). Keep existing branch/JAL/misalign logic unchanged.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n  \"fitness\": 297.42,\n  \"delta_pct\": -8.23,\n  \"vs_baseline\": 5.16,\n  \"fmax_mhz\": 126.28,\n  \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06,\n  \"cycles\": 4245805,\n  \"iterations\": 10,\n  \"lut4\": 10086,\n  \"ff\": 1950,\n  \"seeds\": [\n    123.23,\n    135.1,\n    126.28\n  ],\n  \"formal_passed\": true,\n  \"cosim_passed\": true,\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"implementation_notes\": \"\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T02:34:32.311729Z\",\n  \"slot\": 2,\n  \"round_id\": 2,\n  \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"\n}\n","exit":0,"description":"Print log entry for RAS predictor","truncated":false},"title":"Print log entry for RAS predictor","time":{"start":1778731693074,"end":1778731693075}},"id":"prt_e24abaed8001Y3uPV329rfZLel","sessionID":"ses_1db556982ffeOpDgGDUzASRGrB","messageID":"msg_e24ab52fa001FVuL0r89uvcF3N"}}
