eld to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add a 5-bit ghr register initialised to 0.\n      Update it on every EX-stage branch resolution by shifting in\n      bht_update_taken (ghr <= {ghr[3:0], bht_update_taken}).\n      Replace the BHT read index pc[6:2] with pc[6:2] ^ ghr.\n      Drive the current ghr value into the combinational if_id_t output.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Capture in.ghr into the ID/EX register so the snapshot reaches EX.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Compute BHT update index as in.pc[6:2] ^ in.ghr so the counter update\n      writes the exact entry that was read during fetch.\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778733125078,"end":1778733125084}},"id":"prt_e24c16600001gC6tKFQnG4UEBB","sessionID":"ses_1db419780ffePQX9n0RRVocN9K","messageID":"msg_e24c154fb001GEVC7AN5D24QOm"}}
