{"type":"text","timestamp":1778733132727,"sessionID":"ses_1db419780ffePQX9n0RRVocN9K","part":{"id":"prt_e24c19c51001yc5WlqSRWyah11","messageID":"msg_e24c19016001bi2KUCdNQ9ZE5Q","sessionID":"ses_1db419780ffePQX9n0RRVocN9K","type":"text","text":"Done. I wrote the hypothesis YAML for **hyp-20260514-003-r6s2** at:\n\n`cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r6s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary of the proposal:**\n- **Category:** predictor\n- **Idea:** Upgrade the existing 32-entry bimodal BHT to a minimal **gshare** predictor by XORing a 5-bit Global History Register (GHR) into the BHT index (`pc[6:2] ^ ghr[4:0]`).\n- **Why:** A prior 128-entry BHT attempt tried to reduce aliasing but regressed fitness because the larger read mux hurt Fmax. Gshare solves aliasing without enlarging the table (still 32 entries, same 32:1 mux), so Fmax stays essentially unchanged while improving prediction accuracy for correlated branches.\n- **Cost:** 5 flops for the GHR + 5 bits pipelined through IF/ID and ID/EX. Negligible combinational delay.\n- **Expected impact:** +2% fitness (medium confidence).","time":{"start":1778733128785,"end":1778733132726}}}
