{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778736122488,"sessionID":"ses_1db13f553ffeCMpsVuqxYIOVLU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"id: hyp-20260514-003-r7s2\ntitle: Fix gshare by speculatively updating GHR in IF with mispredict restore\nmotivation: |\n  The prior 32-entry BHT added +7.3% fitness, but a follow-up gshare variant\n  regressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated non-speculatively in EX. By the\n  time a branch resolved, the next branch had already been fetched with stale\n  history, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark contains short basic blocks\n  with back-to-back branches where history staleness is fatal.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace the non-speculative EX-stage GHR update with a speculative IF-stage\n  update plus EX-stage restore on mispredict. A 5-bit GHR register in IF is\n  shifted left with predict_taken whenever a conditional branch is fetched.\n  The pre-update GHR value is snapshotted into a new 5-bit field in the IF/ID\n  and ID/EX bundles. In EX, when a conditional branch mispredicts (redirect),\n  the GHR is restored to {snapshot[3:0], actual_taken}; on correct prediction\n  the speculative update is already exact and needs no action. The BHT read\n  index remains pc[6:2] ^ ghr and the update index remains pc[6:2] ^ snapshot.\n  This gives the 32-entry BHT history-aware indexing without any Fmax penalty\n  from a larger array, and fixes the staleness that broke the first gshare.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add a 5-bit ghr_snapshot field to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Add a 5-bit ghr register initialised to 0.\n      Compute BHT read index as pc[6:2] ^ ghr.\n      Drive the current ghr value into out.ghr_snapshot.\n      On non-stalled, non-flushed cycles where the fetched instruction is a\n      conditional branch, speculatively update ghr <= {ghr[3:0], predict_taken}.\n      Add a new input port ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en; when restore_en\n      is asserted on redirect from EX, reload ghr with ghr_restore.\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Capture in.ghr_snapshot into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: >\n      Compute BHT update index as in.pc[6:2] ^ in.ghr_snapshot so the counter\n      update writes the exact entry that was read during fetch.\n      Add output ports ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en.\n      Drive ghr_restore = {in.ghr_snapshot[3:0], branch_taken} and assert\n      ghr_restore_en whenever redirect is asserted for a conditional branch\n      (in.ctrl.is_branch). JAL/JALR redirects must not assert restore_en.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire the new ghr_restore/ghr_restore_en signals from ex_stage back to if_stage.\"\n","filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778736122478,"end":1778736122486}},"id":"prt_e24ef1388001YyealH2pp9orod","sessionID":"ses_1db13f553ffeCMpsVuqxYIOVLU","messageID":"msg_e24eea7f3001rTOoBGQ2xPVV5X"}}
