{"type":"text","timestamp":1778736129809,"sessionID":"ses_1db13f553ffeCMpsVuqxYIOVLU","part":{"id":"prt_e24ef5c88001nS2w1CXm39CTJd","messageID":"msg_e24ef4bd7001LAuZyXL9DdogrD","sessionID":"ses_1db13f553ffeCMpsVuqxYIOVLU","type":"text","text":"Wrote hypothesis file: `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml`\n\n**Summary:** Fixes the failed gshare attempt by moving GHR updates from EX to IF (speculative, on fetch) and adding a mispredict-restore path from EX. This eliminates the stale-history problem that caused back-to-back branches to alias destructively, while keeping the proven 32-entry BHT size so Fmax is unaffected.","time":{"start":1778736127112,"end":1778736129807}}}
