{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778739680916,"sessionID":"ses_1dadf93b3ffeMfaoMLwX4gHiIS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sed -n '7p' /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'outcome|fitness|delta_pct|fmax_mhz|lut4|ff|cycles|error'","description":"Extract RAS hypothesis outcome"},"output":"        \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\\ninstruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\\nfetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\\npop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\\npred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\\nID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\\nredirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\\ndiffers from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\\nnon-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\\nreturns.\\n\",\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n    \"fitness\": 297.42,\n    \"delta_pct\": -8.23,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 126.28,\n    \"cycles\": 4245805,\n    \"lut4\": 10086,\n    \"ff\": 1950,\n    \"error\": null,\n","metadata":{"output":"        \"hypothesis\": \"Extend the IF-stage predictor with a 4-entry RAS. When the fetched\\ninstruction is a JAL with rd=x1 or x5, push PC+4 onto the stack. When the\\nfetched instruction is a JALR with rs1=x1 or x5 and the stack is non-empty,\\npop the top entry and treat it as the predicted target (pred_taken=1,\\npred_target=ras_top). Thread the predicted target through the IF/ID and\\nID/EX bundles so that EX can verify it. In EX, a JALR only causes a\\nredirect when it was unpredicted (!pred_taken) or when the actual target\\ndiffers from pred_target. The RAS pointer is updated only on non-stalled,\\nnon-flushed cycles. This removes the bubble on the vast majority of\\nreturns.\\n\",\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 3,\n    \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n    \"fitness\": 297.42,\n    \"delta_pct\": -8.23,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 126.28,\n    \"cycles\": 4245805,\n    \"lut4\": 10086,\n    \"ff\": 1950,\n    \"error\": null,\n","exit":0,"description":"Extract RAS hypothesis outcome","truncated":false},"title":"Extract RAS hypothesis outcome","time":{"start":1778739680914,"end":1778739680915}},"id":"prt_e25258fe4001kLwtx24DX7doEr","sessionID":"ses_1dadf93b3ffeMfaoMLwX4gHiIS","messageID":"msg_e252555c0001SGexqWeybYey8E"}}
