{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778739765652,"sessionID":"ses_1dadf93b3ffeMfaoMLwX4gHiIS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"functions.bash:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"sed -n '4p' /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl | python3 -m json.tool | grep -E 'outcome|fitness|delta_pct|fmax_mhz|lut4|ff|cycles|error'","description":"Extract ID-stage static predictor outcome"},"output":"        \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\",\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n    \"fitness\": 282.82,\n    \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03,\n    \"cycles\": 4491485,\n    \"lut4\": 9563,\n    \"ff\": 1866,\n    \"error\": null,\n","metadata":{"output":"        \"hypothesis\": \"Add a simple static predictor in the ID stage that:\\n1) Predicts JAL (unconditional jump) always taken.\\n2) Predicts conditional branches as taken iff the immediate is negative (backward).\\n3) Redirects the IF PC and flushes the combinational IF/ID output in the same cycle\\n   the branch/jump is in ID.  A `predict_taken` bit is carried through ID/EX so that\\n   EX only asserts `redirect` on a mispredict (predicted-not-taken but taken, or\\n   predicted-taken but not-taken).  JALR is intentionally *not* predicted because its\\n   target depends on `rs1`, which may still be pending from an in-flight ALU result\\n (forwarding only exists in EX, not ID).\\n\\nThis turns the common-case loop-back branch from a 2-cycle penalty into 0 cycles,\\nand unconditional JAL from 2 cycles to 0 cycles, while keeping forward branches and\\nJALR at their existing penalties.\\n\",\n            \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": 10,\n    \"outcome\": \"regression\",\n    \"fitness\": 282.82,\n    \"delta_pct\": 0.0,\n    \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03,\n    \"cycles\": 4491485,\n    \"lut4\": 9563,\n    \"ff\": 1866,\n    \"error\": null,\n","exit":0,"description":"Extract ID-stage static predictor outcome","truncated":false},"title":"Extract ID-stage static predictor outcome","time":{"start":1778739765650,"end":1778739765651}},"id":"prt_e2526dab60011S3ZYhtJKMR0I9","sessionID":"ses_1dadf93b3ffeMfaoMLwX4gHiIS","messageID":"msg_e2526cbb70014GqTjHnzjHmPUE"}}
