ime [H:MM:SS (secs)]: 0:00:08 (8)\\nSBY  2:58:03 [reg_ch0] summary: engine_0 (smtbmc bitwuzla) returned FAIL\\nSBY  2:58:03 [reg_ch0] summary: counterexample trace: reg_ch0/engine_0/trace.vcd\\nSBY  2:58:03 [reg_ch0] summary:   failed assertion rvfi_testbench._witness_.check_flatten_checker_inst__assert_rvfi_reg_check_sv_44_62 at rvfi_reg_check.sv:44.6-44.59 step 20\\nSBY  2:58:03 [reg_ch0] DONE (FAIL, rc=0)\\n\\nFull run log: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0/formal/last_run-63200.log\\nPer-check logs in: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260514-001-r7s0/formal/riscv-formal/cores/bench-63200/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 7, \"scribe_skipped\": \"TimeoutError: scribe timed out after 240s\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r7s1\", \"title\": \"Replace combinational divider with iterative multi-cycle unit\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The current ALU infers a full 32-bit combinational divider from the\\nSystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. Flattened synthesis shows the EX\\nstage alone consumes over 6000 cells (52 % of the entire core) and is\\ndominated by arithmetic primitives. Division is essentially unused in\\nCoreMark, yet the combinational divider consumes massive area and\\nrouting resources that congest the fabric around the critical ALU adder\\npath, limiting Fmax. A prior attempt at this change failed because the\\ndivider state machine lacked a proper IDLE/RUNNING/DONE FSM with a\\n'started' bit, causing deadlock. With a correct FSM implementation,\\nremoving the combinational divider should relieve routing congestion\\nand raise Fmax with negligible IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current ALU infers a full 32-bit combinational divider from the\\nSystemVerilog `/` and `%` operators. Flattened synthesis shows the EX\\nstage alone consumes over 6000 cells (52 % of the entire core) and is\\ndominated by arithmetic primitives. Division is essentially unused in\\nCoreMark, yet the combinational divider consumes massive area and\\nrouting resources that congest the fabric around the critical ALU adder\\npath, limiting Fmax. A prior attempt at this change failed because the\\ndivider state machine lacked a proper IDLE/RUNNING/DONE FSM with a\\n'started' bit, causing deadlock. With a correct FSM implementation,\\nremoving the combinational divider should relieve routing congestion\\nand raise Fmax with negligible IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Extract DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU out of the combinational ALU into a new\\n`divider.sv` module that performs restoring division in 33 cycles.\\nThe divider MUST use a proper 3-state FSM (IDLE, RUNNING, DONE) with\\na registered 'started' bit:\\n  - IDLE:  waiting for start pulse. busy=0, done=0.\\n  - RUNNING: counting down 32 bits. busy=1, done=0.\\n  - DONE: result valid for one cycle. busy=0, done=1. Next clock\\n    returns to IDLE automatically.\\nIn `ex_stage`, detect divide ops and assert `div_start` for exactly\\none cycle when the divider is in IDLE. The hazard unit stalls IF,\\nID, and EX/MEM while `div_busy` (= RUNNING) is high. Because `busy`\\nis LOW in the DONE state, the EX/MEM register naturally captures the\\ndivider result on the done cycle and the next instruction can enter\\nEX on the following cycle. The main ALU keeps all I-type ops and the\\nmultiplier path. This structural change shrinks the EX stage\\nsignificantly, frees routing capacity on the critical path, and\\nshould improve median Fmax without hurting CoreMark IPC.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases and all combinational divide/rem\\nlogic. Keep the multiplier paths and the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\\nbranch unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/divider.sv\", \"description\": \"New iterative restoring divider with IDLE/RUNNING/DONE FSM.\\nInputs: clock, reset, start, dividend[31:0], divisor[31:0],\\nop[3:0] selecting DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU. Outputs: result[31:0],\\nbusy, done. 33-cycle latency. busy is high only in RUNNING.\\ndone is high for one cycle in DONE. Returns to IDLE on next\\nclock edge. Handles all RV32M corner cases (divide by zero,\\nINT_MIN/-1).\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect divide ops from in.ctrl.alu_op. Route operands to the\\ndivider and assert div_start when the divider is idle.\\nCapture divider result into ex_mem_w.alu_result when div_done\\nis high. Stall EX/MEM via hazard_unit during div_busy.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add div_busy input. Extend stall_if, stall_id, and stall_ex_mem\\nto freeze the entire pipeline while div_busy is high. Do not\\nassert flush_id during div_busy; hold the pipeline state.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate divider module. Wire div_busy into hazard_unit.\\nConnect divider inputs from id_ex_w operands. No top-level IO\\nchanges.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU cases and all combinational divide/rem\\nlogic. Keep the multiplier paths and the RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS\\nbranch unchanged.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/divider.sv\", \"description\": \"New iterative restoring divider with IDLE/RUNNING/DONE FSM.\\nInputs: clock, reset, start, dividend[31:0], divisor[31:0],\\nop[3:0] selecting DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU. Outputs: result[31:0],\\nbusy, done. 33-cycle latency. busy is high only in RUNNING.\\ndone is high for one cycle in DONE. Returns to IDLE on next\\nclock edge. Handles all RV32M corner cases (divide by zero,\\nINT_MIN/-1).\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Detect divide ops from in.ctrl.alu_op. Route operands to the\\ndivider and assert div_start when the divider is idle.\\nCapture divider result into ex_mem_w.alu_result when div_done\\nis high. Stall EX/MEM via hazard_unit during div_busy.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add div_busy input. Extend stall_if, stall_id, and stall_ex_mem\\nto freeze the entire pipeline while div_busy is high. Do not\\nassert flush_id during div_busy; hold the pipeline state.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate divider module. Wire div_busy into hazard_unit.\\nConnect divider inputs from id_ex_w operands. No top-level IO\\nchanges.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 347.76, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 22.96, \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4203461, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10254, \"ff\": 1940, \"seeds\": [146.18, 132.82, 146.26], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:07:59.336648Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 7, \"scribe_skipped\": \"PermissionError: scribe touched off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/core.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv', 'cores/bench/rtl/hazard_unit.sv', 'cores/bench/test/test_alu.py', 'cores/bench/test/test_pipeline.py', 'cores/bench/rtl/divider.sv', 'cores/bench/test/test_divider.py']\"}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r7s2\", \"title\": \"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/kimi-k2_6-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260514-003-r7s2.yaml\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"schema_error: 'category' is a required property\\n\\nFailed validating 'required' in schema:\\n    {'$schema': 'http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#',\\n     'type': 'object',\\n     'required': ['id',\\n                  'title',\\n                  'category',\\n                  'motivation',\\n                  'hypothesis',\\n                  'expected_impact',\\n                  'changes'],\\n     'properties': {'id': {'type': 'string',\\n                           'pattern': '^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$'},\\n                    'title': {'type': 'string', 'minLength': 5},\\n                    'category': {'type': 'string',\\n                                 'enum': ['micro_opt',\\n                                          'structural',\\n                                          'extension',\\n                                          'predictor',\\n                                          'memory']},\\n                    'motivation': {'type': 'string', 'minLength': 20},\\n                    'hypothesis': {'type': 'string', 'minLength': 20},\\n                    'expected_impact': {'type': 'object',\\n                                        'required': ['fitness_delta_pct',\\n                                                     'confidence'],\\n                                        'properties': {'fitness_delta_pct': {'type': 'integer'},\\n                                                       'confidence': {'type': 'string',\\n                                                                      'enum': ['low',\\n                                                                               'medium',\\n                                                                               'high']}}},\\n                    'changes': {'type': 'array',\\n                                'minItems': 1,\\n                                'items': {'type': 'object',\\n                                          'required': ['file',\\n                                                       'description'],\\n                                          'properties': {'file': {'type': 'string',\\n                                                                  'description': 'Must '\\n                                                                                 'be '\\n                                                                                 'under '\\n                                                                                 'rtl/ '\\n                                                                                 '(any '\\n                                                                                 'extension) '\\n                                                                                 'or '\\n                                                                                 'be '\\n                                                                                 'a '\\n                                                                                 'test/test_*.py '\\n                                                                                 'cocotb '\\n                                                                                 'suite. '\\n                                                                                 'Anything '\\n                                                                                 'else '\\n                                                                                 'is '\\n                                                                                 'rejected '\\n                                                                                 'by '\\n                                                                                 'the '\\n                                                                                 'runtime '\\n                                                                                 'sandbox '\\n                                                                                 'check.',\\n                                                                  'pattern': '^(rtl/[^.].*|test/test_[^/]+\\\\\\\\.py)$'},\\n                                                         'description': {'type': 'string'}}}}}}\\n\\nOn instance:\\n    {'id': 'hyp-20260514-003-r7s2',\\n     'title': 'Fix gshare by speculatively updating GHR in IF with '\\n              'mispredict restore',\\n     'motivation': 'The prior 32-entry BHT added +7.3% fitness, but a '\\n                   'follow-up gshare variant\\\\n'\\n                   'regressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated '\\n                   'non-speculatively in EX. By the\\\\n'\\n                   'time a branch resolved, the next branch had already '\\n                   'been fetched with stale\\\\n'\\n                   'history, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark '\\n                   'contains short basic blocks\\\\n'\\n                   'with back-to-back branches where history staleness is '\\n                   'fatal.\\\\n',\\n     'hypothesis': 'Replace the non-speculative EX-stage GHR update with a '\\n                   'speculative IF-stage\\\\n'\\n                   'update plus EX-stage restore on mispredict. A 5-bit '\\n                   'GHR register in IF is\\\\n'\\n                   'shifted left with predict_taken whenever a conditional '\\n                   'branch is fetched.\\\\n'\\n                   'The pre-update GHR value is snapshotted into a new '\\n                   '5-bit field in the IF/ID\\\\n'\\n                   'and ID/EX bundles. In EX, when a conditional branch '\\n                   'mispredicts (redirect),\\\\n'\\n                   'the GHR is restored to {snapshot[3:0], actual_taken}; '\\n                   'on correct prediction\\\\n'\\n                   'the speculative update is already exact and needs no '\\n                   'action. The BHT read\\\\n'\\n                   'index remains pc[6:2] ^ ghr and the update index '\\n                   'remains pc[6:2] ^ snapshot.\\\\n'\\n                   'This gives the 32-entry BHT history-aware indexing '\\n                   'without any Fmax penalty\\\\n'\\n                   'from a larger array, and fixes the staleness that '\\n                   'broke the first gshare.\\\\n',\\n     'expected_impact': {'fitness_delta_pct': 4, 'confidence': 'medium'},\\n     'changes': [{'file': 'rtl/core_pkg.sv',\\n                  'description': 'Add a 5-bit ghr_snapshot field to '\\n                                 'if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.'},\\n                 {'file': 'rtl/if_stage.sv',\\n                  'description': 'Add a 5-bit ghr register initialised to '\\n                                 '0. Compute BHT read index as pc[6:2] ^ '\\n                                 'ghr. Drive the current ghr value into '\\n                                 'out.ghr_snapshot. On non-stalled, '\\n                                 'non-flushed cycles where the fetched '\\n                                 'instruction is a conditional branch, '\\n                                 'speculatively update ghr <= {ghr[3:0], '\\n                                 'predict_taken}. Add a new input port '\\n                                 'ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en; '\\n                                 'when restore_en is asserted on redirect '\\n                                 'from EX, reload ghr with ghr_restore.\\\\n'},\\n                 {'file': 'rtl/id_stage.sv',\\n                  'description': 'Capture in.ghr_snapshot into the ID/EX '\\n                                 'register so it reaches EX.'},\\n                 {'file': 'rtl/ex_stage.sv',\\n                  'description': 'Compute BHT update index as in.pc[6:2] ^ '\\n                                 'in.ghr_snapshot so the counter update '\\n                                 'writes the exact entry that was read '\\n                                 'during fetch. Add output ports '\\n                                 'ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en. '\\n                                 'Drive ghr_restore = '\\n                                 '{in.ghr_snapshot[3:0], branch_taken} and '\\n                                 'assert ghr_restore_en whenever redirect '\\n                                 'is asserted for a conditional branch '\\n                                 '(in.ctrl.is_branch). JAL/JALR redirects '\\n                                 'must not assert restore_en.\\\\n'},\\n                 {'file': 'rtl/core.sv',\\n                  'description': 'Wire the new ghr_restore/ghr_restore_en '\\n                                 'signals from ex_stage back to '\\n                                 'if_stage.'}]}\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 7, \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The prior 32-entry BHT added +7.3% fitness, but a follow-up gshare variant\\nregressed -6.7% because its GHR was updated non-speculatively in EX. By the\\ntime a branch resolved, the next branch had already been fetched with stale\\nhistory, increasing destructive aliasing. CoreMark contains short basic blocks\\nwith back-to-back branches where history staleness is fatal.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the non-speculative EX-stage GHR update with a speculative IF-stage\\nupdate plus EX-stage restore on mispredict. A 5-bit GHR register in IF is\\nshifted left with predict_taken whenever a conditional branch is fetched.\\nThe pre-update GHR value is snapshotted into a new 5-bit field in the IF/ID\\nand ID/EX bundles. In EX, when a conditional branch mispredicts (redirect),\\nthe GHR is restored to {snapshot[3:0], actual_taken}; on correct prediction\\nthe speculative update is already exact and needs no action. The BHT read\\nindex remains pc[6:2] ^ ghr and the update index remains pc[6:2] ^ snapshot.\\nThis gives the 32-entry BHT history-aware indexing without any Fmax penalty\\nfrom a larger array, and fixes the staleness that broke the first gshare.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 4, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 5-bit ghr_snapshot field to if_id_t and id_ex_t pipeline bundles.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a 5-bit ghr register initialised to 0. Compute BHT read index as pc[6:2] ^ ghr. Drive the current ghr value into out.ghr_snapshot. On non-stalled, non-flushed cycles where the fetched instruction is a conditional branch, speculatively update ghr <= {ghr[3:0], predict_taken}. Add a new input port ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en; when restore_en is asserted on redirect from EX, reload ghr with ghr_restore.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Capture in.ghr_snapshot into the ID/EX register so it reaches EX.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Compute BHT update index as in.pc[6:2] ^ in.ghr_snapshot so the counter update writes the exact entry that was read during fetch. Add output ports ghr_restore[4:0] and ghr_restore_en. Drive ghr_restore = {in.ghr_snapshot[3:0], branch_taken} and assert ghr_restore_en whenever redirect is asserted for a conditional branch (in.ctrl.is_branch). JAL/JALR redirects must not assert restore_en.\\n\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire the new ghr_restore/ghr_restore_en signals from ex_stage back to if_stage.\"}]}}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-001-r8s0\", \"title\": \"Consolidate ALU multipliers to reduce routing congestion and improve Fmax\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current ALU unconditionally computes three separate 64-bit products\\n(mul_ss, mul_uu, mul_su) on every cycle even though only one multiply\\nop is ever active.  On FPGA this causes the synthesis tool to infer\\nmultiple wide multipliers and large cross-products that consume DSP\\nblocks and routing resources around the EX stage.  CoreMark is\\nmultiply-heavy (matrix operations), so the ALU multiplier path is\\nlikely on or near the critical path.  By sharing a single 64-bit\\nmultiplier and selecting the signedness mode per-op, we cut the\\nmultiplier area by roughly two thirds and relieve routing\\ncongestion, which should raise median Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current ALU unconditionally computes three separate 64-bit products\\n(mul_ss, mul_uu, mul_su) on every cycle even though only one multiply\\nop is ever active.  On FPGA this causes the synthesis tool to infer\\nmultiple wide multipliers and large cross-products that consume DSP\\nblocks and routing resources around the EX stage.  CoreMark is\\nmultiply-heavy (matrix operations), so the ALU multiplier path is\\nlikely on or near the critical path.  By sharing a single 64-bit\\nmultiplier and selecting the signedness mode per-op, we cut the\\nmultiplier area by roughly two thirds and relieve routing\\ncongestion, which should raise median Fmax with zero IPC impact.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Replace the three always-computed 64-bit products in alu.sv with one\\nshared 64-bit multiplier whose operands are muxed per the active ALU\\nop: unsigned*unsigned for MUL/MULHU, signed*signed for MULH, and\\nsigned*unsigned for MULHSU.  Add a small case block before the\\nmultiplication that selects the correctly-extended a and b inputs.\\nThe DIV/REM family remains combinational (unchanged); only the MUL\\nfamily is touched.  This reduces inferred multiplier count from three\\nto one, shrinking EX-stage area and easing nextpnr placement.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the three always-on 64-bit product wires (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su).  Add a shared 64-bit `mul_result` wire.  Precede the\\nmultiply with a combinational mux that selects the sign-extended\\noperands based on the current ALU op, then assign mul_result once.\\nUpdate the MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU case arms to pick the correct\\nhigh or low half of mul_result.  Keep the ALTOPS branch intact.\\n\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 3, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the three always-on 64-bit product wires (mul_ss, mul_uu,\\nmul_su).  Add a shared 64-bit `mul_result` wire.  Precede the\\nmultiply with a combinational mux that selects the sign-extended\\noperands based on the current ALU op, then assign mul_result once.\\nUpdate the MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU case arms to pick the correct\\nhigh or low half of mul_result.  Keep the ALTOPS branch intact.\\n\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 347.76, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 22.96, \"fmax_mhz\": 146.18, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4203461, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 10254, \"ff\": 1940, \"seeds\": [146.18, 132.82, 146.26], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-14T06:38:10.504767Z\", \"slot\": 0, \"round_id\": 8}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-002-r8s1\", \"title\": \"(slot 1 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent modified off-limits paths and was rolled back: ['cores/bench/rtl/alu.sv']\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 8}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260514-003-r8s2\", \"title\": \"(slot 2 hypothesis-gen failed)\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"outcome\": \"broken\", \"formal_passed\": false, \"cosim_passed\": false, \"error\": \"hypothesis_gen_failed: Hypothesis agent did not write a file for slot hyp-20260514-003-r8s2 (allowed_yaml_ids=['hyp-20260514-001-r8s0', 'hyp-20260514-002-r8s1', 'hyp-20260514-003-r8s2'])\", \"slot\": 2, \"round_id\": 8}\n","exit":0,"description":"Grep GHR attempt details","truncated":false},"title":"Grep GHR attempt details","time":{"start":1778741370471,"end":1778741370474}},"id":"prt_e253f5b43001lbsb0vj2UyaGFk","sessionID":"ses_1dac84df8ffeqy1fd7OqLOZiN1","messageID":"msg_e253e1aee001A9z1ihVAZeCoOe"}}
